2174static APInt readWideAPInt(ArrayRef<uint64_t> Vals, unsigned TypeBits) {
2175 SmallVector<uint64_t, 8> Words(Vals.size());
2176 transform(Vals, Words.begin(),
2177 BitcodeReader::decodeSignRotatedValue);
2178
2179 return APInt(TypeBits, Words);
2180}
2181
2182Error BitcodeReader::parseConstants() {
2183 if (Stream.EnterSubBlock(bitc::CONSTANTS_BLOCK_ID))
2184 return error("Invalid record");
2185
2186 SmallVector<uint64_t, 64> Record;
2187
2188 // Read all the records for this value table.
2189 Type *CurTy = Type::getInt32Ty(Context);
2190 unsigned NextCstNo = ValueList.size();
2191
2192 while (true) {
2193 BitstreamEntry Entry = Stream.advanceSkippingSubblocks();
2194
2195 switch (Entry.Kind) {
2196 case BitstreamEntry::SubBlock: // Handled for us already.
2197 case BitstreamEntry::Error:
2198 return error("Malformed block");
2199 case BitstreamEntry::EndBlock:
2200 if (NextCstNo != ValueList.size())
2201 return error("Invalid constant reference");
2202
2203 // Once all the constants have been read, go through and resolve forward
2204 // references.
2205 ValueList.resolveConstantForwardRefs();
2206 return Error::success();
2207 case BitstreamEntry::Record:
2208 // The interesting case.
2209 break;
2210 }
2211
2212 // Read a record.
2213 Record.clear();
2214 Type *VoidType = Type::getVoidTy(Context);
2215 Value *V = nullptr;
2216 unsigned BitCode = Stream.readRecord(Entry.ID, Record);
2217 switch (BitCode) {
2218 default: // Default behavior: unknown constant
2219 case bitc::CST_CODE_UNDEF: // UNDEF
2220 V = UndefValue::get(CurTy);
2221 break;
2222 case bitc::CST_CODE_SETTYPE: // SETTYPE: [typeid]
2223 if (Record.empty())
2224 return error("Invalid record");
2225 if (Record[0] >= TypeList.size() || !TypeList[Record[0]])
2226 return error("Invalid record");
2227 if (TypeList[Record[0]] == VoidType)
2228 return error("Invalid constant type");
2229 CurTy = TypeList[Record[0]];
2230 continue; // Skip the ValueList manipulation.
2231 case bitc::CST_CODE_NULL: // NULL
2232 V = Constant::getNullValue(CurTy);
2233 break;
2234 case bitc::CST_CODE_INTEGER: // INTEGER: [intval]
2235 if (!CurTy->isIntegerTy() || Record.empty())
2236 return error("Invalid record");
2237 V = ConstantInt::get(CurTy, decodeSignRotatedValue(Record[0]));
2238 break;
2239 case bitc::CST_CODE_WIDE_INTEGER: {// WIDE_INTEGER: [n x intval]
2240 if (!CurTy->isIntegerTy() || Record.empty())
2241 return error("Invalid record");
2242
2243 APInt VInt =
2244 readWideAPInt(Record, cast<IntegerType>(CurTy)->getBitWidth());
2245 V = ConstantInt::get(Context, VInt);
2246
2247 break;
2248 }
2249 case bitc::CST_CODE_FLOAT: { // FLOAT: [fpval]
2250 if (Record.empty())
2251 return error("Invalid record");
2252 if (CurTy->isHalfTy())
2253 V = ConstantFP::get(Context, APFloat(APFloat::IEEEhalf(),
2254 APInt(16, (uint16_t)Record[0])));
2255 else if (CurTy->isFloatTy())
2256 V = ConstantFP::get(Context, APFloat(APFloat::IEEEsingle(),
2257 APInt(32, (uint32_t)Record[0])));
2258 else if (CurTy->isDoubleTy())
2259 V = ConstantFP::get(Context, APFloat(APFloat::IEEEdouble(),
2260 APInt(64, Record[0])));
2261 else if (CurTy->isX86_FP80Ty()) {
2262 // Bits are not stored the same way as a normal i80 APInt, compensate.
2263 uint64_t Rearrange[2];
2264 Rearrange[0] = (Record[1] & 0xffffLL) | (Record[0] << 16);
2265 Rearrange[1] = Record[0] >> 48;
2266 V = ConstantFP::get(Context, APFloat(APFloat::x87DoubleExtended(),
2267 APInt(80, Rearrange)));
2268 } else if (CurTy->isFP128Ty())
2269 V = ConstantFP::get(Context, APFloat(APFloat::IEEEquad(),
2270 APInt(128, Record)));
2271 else if (CurTy->isPPC_FP128Ty())
2272 V = ConstantFP::get(Context, APFloat(APFloat::PPCDoubleDouble(),
2273 APInt(128, Record)));
2274 else
2275 V = UndefValue::get(CurTy);
2276 break;
2277 }
2278
2279 case bitc::CST_CODE_AGGREGATE: {// AGGREGATE: [n x value number]
2280 if (Record.empty())
2281 return error("Invalid record");
2282
2283 unsigned Size = Record.size();
2284 SmallVector<Constant*, 16> Elts;
2285
2286 if (StructType *STy = dyn_cast<StructType>(CurTy)) {
2287 for (unsigned i = 0; i != Size; ++i)
2288 Elts.push_back(ValueList.getConstantFwdRef(Record[i],
2289 STy->getElementType(i)));
2290 V = ConstantStruct::get(STy, Elts);
2291 } else if (ArrayType *ATy = dyn_cast<ArrayType>(CurTy)) {
2292 Type *EltTy = ATy->getElementType();
2293 for (unsigned i = 0; i != Size; ++i)
2294 Elts.push_back(ValueList.getConstantFwdRef(Record[i], EltTy));
2295 V = ConstantArray::get(ATy, Elts);
2296 } else if (VectorType *VTy = dyn_cast<VectorType>(CurTy)) {
2297 Type *EltTy = VTy->getElementType();
2298 for (unsigned i = 0; i != Size; ++i)
2299 Elts.push_back(ValueList.getConstantFwdRef(Record[i], EltTy));
2300 V = ConstantVector::get(Elts);
2301 } else {
2302 V = UndefValue::get(CurTy);
2303 }
2304 break;
2305 }
2306 case bitc::CST_CODE_STRING: // STRING: [values]
2307 case bitc::CST_CODE_CSTRING: { // CSTRING: [values]
2308 if (Record.empty())
2309 return error("Invalid record");
2310
2311 SmallString<16> Elts(Record.begin(), Record.end());
2312 V = ConstantDataArray::getString(Context, Elts,
2313 BitCode == bitc::CST_CODE_CSTRING);
2314 break;
2315 }
2316 case bitc::CST_CODE_DATA: {// DATA: [n x value]
2317 if (Record.empty())
2318 return error("Invalid record");
2319
2320 Type *EltTy = cast<SequentialType>(CurTy)->getElementType();
2321 if (EltTy->isIntegerTy(8)) {
2322 SmallVector<uint8_t, 16> Elts(Record.begin(), Record.end());
2323 if (isa<VectorType>(CurTy))
2324 V = ConstantDataVector::get(Context, Elts);
2325 else
2326 V = ConstantDataArray::get(Context, Elts);
2327 } else if (EltTy->isIntegerTy(16)) {
2328 SmallVector<uint16_t, 16> Elts(Record.begin(), Record.end());
2329 if (isa<VectorType>(CurTy))
2330 V = ConstantDataVector::get(Context, Elts);
2331 else
2332 V = ConstantDataArray::get(Context, Elts);
2333 } else if (EltTy->isIntegerTy(32)) {
2334 SmallVector<uint32_t, 16> Elts(Record.begin(), Record.end());
2335 if (isa<VectorType>(CurTy))
2336 V = ConstantDataVector::get(Context, Elts);
2337 else
2338 V = ConstantDataArray::get(Context, Elts);
2339 } else if (EltTy->isIntegerTy(64)) {
2340 SmallVector<uint64_t, 16> Elts(Record.begin(), Record.end());
2341 if (isa<VectorType>(CurTy))
2342 V = ConstantDataVector::get(Context, Elts);
2343 else
2344 V = ConstantDataArray::get(Context, Elts);
2345 } else if (EltTy->isHalfTy()) {
2346 SmallVector<uint16_t, 16> Elts(Record.begin(), Record.end());
2347 if (isa<VectorType>(CurTy))
2348 V = ConstantDataVector::getFP(Context, Elts);
2349 else
2350 V = ConstantDataArray::getFP(Context, Elts);
2351 } else if (EltTy->isFloatTy()) {
2352 SmallVector<uint32_t, 16> Elts(Record.begin(), Record.end());
2353 if (isa<VectorType>(CurTy))
2354 V = ConstantDataVector::getFP(Context, Elts);
2355 else
2356 V = ConstantDataArray::getFP(Context, Elts);
2357 } else if (EltTy->isDoubleTy()) {
2358 SmallVector<uint64_t, 16> Elts(Record.begin(), Record.end());
2359 if (isa<VectorType>(CurTy))
2360 V = ConstantDataVector::getFP(Context, Elts);
2361 else
2362 V = ConstantDataArray::getFP(Context, Elts);
2363 } else {
2364 return error("Invalid type for value");
2365 }
2366 break;
2367 }
2368 case bitc::CST_CODE_CE_UNOP: { // CE_UNOP: [opcode, opval]
2369 if (Record.size() < 2)
2370 return error("Invalid record");
2371 int Opc = getDecodedUnaryOpcode(Record[0], CurTy);
2372 if (Opc < 0) {
2373 V = UndefValue::get(CurTy); // Unknown unop.
2374 } else {
2375 Constant *LHS = ValueList.getConstantFwdRef(Record[1], CurTy);
2376 unsigned Flags = 0;
2377 V = ConstantExpr::get(Opc, LHS, Flags);
2378 }
2379 break;
2380 }
2381 case bitc::CST_CODE_CE_BINOP: { // CE_BINOP: [opcode, opval, opval]
2382 if (Record.size() < 3)
2383 return error("Invalid record");
2384 int Opc = getDecodedBinaryOpcode(Record[0], CurTy);
2385 if (Opc < 0) {
2386 V = UndefValue::get(CurTy); // Unknown binop.
2387 } else {
2388 Constant *LHS = ValueList.getConstantFwdRef(Record[1], CurTy);
2389 Constant *RHS = ValueList.getConstantFwdRef(Record[2], CurTy);
2390 unsigned Flags = 0;
2391 if (Record.size() >= 4) {
2392 if (Opc == Instruction::Add ||
2393 Opc == Instruction::Sub ||
2394 Opc == Instruction::Mul ||
2395 Opc == Instruction::Shl) {
2396 if (Record[3] & (1 << bitc::OBO_NO_SIGNED_WRAP))
2397 Flags |= OverflowingBinaryOperator::NoSignedWrap;
2398 if (Record[3] & (1 << bitc::OBO_NO_UNSIGNED_WRAP))
2399 Flags |= OverflowingBinaryOperator::NoUnsignedWrap;
2400 } else if (Opc == Instruction::SDiv ||
2401 Opc == Instruction::UDiv ||
2402 Opc == Instruction::LShr ||
2403 Opc == Instruction::AShr) {
2404 if (Record[3] & (1 << bitc::PEO_EXACT))
2405 Flags |= SDivOperator::IsExact;
2406 }
2407 }
2408 V = ConstantExpr::get(Opc, LHS, RHS, Flags);
2409 }
2410 break;
2411 }
2412 case bitc::CST_CODE_CE_CAST: { // CE_CAST: [opcode, opty, opval]
2413 if (Record.size() < 3)
2414 return error("Invalid record");
2415 int Opc = getDecodedCastOpcode(Record[0]);
2416 if (Opc < 0) {
2417 V = UndefValue::get(CurTy); // Unknown cast.
2418 } else {
2419 Type *OpTy = getTypeByID(Record[1]);
2420 if (!OpTy)
2421 return error("Invalid record");
2422 Constant *Op = ValueList.getConstantFwdRef(Record[2], OpTy);
2423 V = UpgradeBitCastExpr(Opc, Op, CurTy);
2424 if (!V) V = ConstantExpr::getCast(Opc, Op, CurTy);
2425 }
2426 break;
2427 }
2428 case bitc::CST_CODE_CE_INBOUNDS_GEP: // [ty, n x operands]
2429 case bitc::CST_CODE_CE_GEP: // [ty, n x operands]
2430 case bitc::CST_CODE_CE_GEP_WITH_INRANGE_INDEX: { // [ty, flags, n x
2431 // operands]
2432 unsigned OpNum = 0;
2433 Type *PointeeType = nullptr;
2434 if (BitCode == bitc::CST_CODE_CE_GEP_WITH_INRANGE_INDEX ||
2435 Record.size() % 2)
2436 PointeeType = getTypeByID(Record[OpNum++]);
2437
2438 bool InBounds = false;
2439 Optional<unsigned> InRangeIndex;
2440 if (BitCode == bitc::CST_CODE_CE_GEP_WITH_INRANGE_INDEX) {
2441 uint64_t Op = Record[OpNum++];
2442 InBounds = Op & 1;
2443 InRangeIndex = Op >> 1;
2444 } else if (BitCode == bitc::CST_CODE_CE_INBOUNDS_GEP)
2445 InBounds = true;
2446
2447 SmallVector<Constant*, 16> Elts;
2448 while (OpNum != Record.size()) {
2449 Type *ElTy = getTypeByID(Record[OpNum++]);
2450 if (!ElTy)
2451 return error("Invalid record");
2452 Elts.push_back(ValueList.getConstantFwdRef(Record[OpNum++], ElTy));
2453 }
2454
2455 if (Elts.size() < 1)
2456 return error("Invalid gep with no operands");
2457
2458 Type *ImplicitPointeeType =
2459 cast<PointerType>(Elts[0]->getType()->getScalarType())
2460 ->getElementType();
2461 if (!PointeeType)
2462 PointeeType = ImplicitPointeeType;
2463 else if (PointeeType != ImplicitPointeeType)
2464 return error("Explicit gep operator type does not match pointee type "
2465 "of pointer operand");
2466
2467 ArrayRef<Constant *> Indices(Elts.begin() + 1, Elts.end());
2468 V = ConstantExpr::getGetElementPtr(PointeeType, Elts[0], Indices,
2469 InBounds, InRangeIndex);
2470 break;
2471 }
2472 case bitc::CST_CODE_CE_SELECT: { // CE_SELECT: [opval#, opval#, opval#]
2473 if (Record.size() < 3)
2474 return error("Invalid record");
2475
2476 Type *SelectorTy = Type::getInt1Ty(Context);
2477
2478 // The selector might be an i1 or an <n x i1>
2479 // Get the type from the ValueList before getting a forward ref.
2480 if (VectorType *VTy = dyn_cast<VectorType>(CurTy))
2481 if (Value *V = ValueList[Record[0]])
2482 if (SelectorTy != V->getType())
2483 SelectorTy = VectorType::get(SelectorTy, VTy->getNumElements());
2484
2485 V = ConstantExpr::getSelect(ValueList.getConstantFwdRef(Record[0],
2486 SelectorTy),
2487 ValueList.getConstantFwdRef(Record[1],CurTy),
2488 ValueList.getConstantFwdRef(Record[2],CurTy));
2489 break;
2490 }
2491 case bitc::CST_CODE_CE_EXTRACTELT
2492 : { // CE_EXTRACTELT: [opty, opval, opty, opval]
2493 if (Record.size() < 3)
2494 return error("Invalid record");
2495 VectorType *OpTy =
2496 dyn_cast_or_null<VectorType>(getTypeByID(Record[0]));
2497 if (!OpTy)
2498 return error("Invalid record");
2499 Constant *Op0 = ValueList.getConstantFwdRef(Record[1], OpTy);
2500 Constant *Op1 = nullptr;
2501 if (Record.size() == 4) {
2502 Type *IdxTy = getTypeByID(Record[2]);
2503 if (!IdxTy)
2504 return error("Invalid record");
2505 Op1 = ValueList.getConstantFwdRef(Record[3], IdxTy);
2506 } else // TODO: Remove with llvm 4.0
2507 Op1 = ValueList.getConstantFwdRef(Record[2], Type::getInt32Ty(Context));
2508 if (!Op1)
2509 return error("Invalid record");
2510 V = ConstantExpr::getExtractElement(Op0, Op1);
2511 break;
2512 }
2513 case bitc::CST_CODE_CE_INSERTELT
2514 : { // CE_INSERTELT: [opval, opval, opty, opval]
2515 VectorType *OpTy = dyn_cast<VectorType>(CurTy);
2516 if (Record.size() < 3 || !OpTy)
2517 return error("Invalid record");
2518 Constant *Op0 = ValueList.getConstantFwdRef(Record[0], OpTy);
2519 Constant *Op1 = ValueList.getConstantFwdRef(Record[1],
2520 OpTy->getElementType());
2521 Constant *Op2 = nullptr;
2522 if (Record.size() == 4) {
2523 Type *IdxTy = getTypeByID(Record[2]);
2524 if (!IdxTy)
2525 return error("Invalid record");
2526 Op2 = ValueList.getConstantFwdRef(Record[3], IdxTy);
2527 } else // TODO: Remove with llvm 4.0
2528 Op2 = ValueList.getConstantFwdRef(Record[2], Type::getInt32Ty(Context));
2529 if (!Op2)
2530 return error("Invalid record");
2531 V = ConstantExpr::getInsertElement(Op0, Op1, Op2);
2532 break;
2533 }
2534 case bitc::CST_CODE_CE_SHUFFLEVEC: { // CE_SHUFFLEVEC: [opval, opval, opval]
2535 VectorType *OpTy = dyn_cast<VectorType>(CurTy);
2536 if (Record.size() < 3 || !OpTy)
2537 return error("Invalid record");
2538 Constant *Op0 = ValueList.getConstantFwdRef(Record[0], OpTy);
2539 Constant *Op1 = ValueList.getConstantFwdRef(Record[1], OpTy);
2540 Type *ShufTy = VectorType::get(Type::getInt32Ty(Context),
2541 OpTy->getNumElements());
2542 Constant *Op2 = ValueList.getConstantFwdRef(Record[2], ShufTy);
2543 V = ConstantExpr::getShuffleVector(Op0, Op1, Op2);
2544 break;
2545 }
2546 case bitc::CST_CODE_CE_SHUFVEC_EX: { // [opty, opval, opval, opval]
2547 VectorType *RTy = dyn_cast<VectorType>(CurTy);
2548 VectorType *OpTy =
2549 dyn_cast_or_null<VectorType>(getTypeByID(Record[0]));
2550 if (Record.size() < 4 || !RTy || !OpTy)
2551 return error("Invalid record");
2552 Constant *Op0 = ValueList.getConstantFwdRef(Record[1], OpTy);
2553 Constant *Op1 = ValueList.getConstantFwdRef(Record[2], OpTy);
2554 Type *ShufTy = VectorType::get(Type::getInt32Ty(Context),
2555 RTy->getNumElements());
2556 Constant *Op2 = ValueList.getConstantFwdRef(Record[3], ShufTy);
2557 V = ConstantExpr::getShuffleVector(Op0, Op1, Op2);
2558 break;
2559 }
2560 case bitc::CST_CODE_CE_CMP: { // CE_CMP: [opty, opval, opval, pred]
2561 if (Record.size() < 4)
2562 return error("Invalid record");
2563 Type *OpTy = getTypeByID(Record[0]);
2564 if (!OpTy)
2565 return error("Invalid record");
2566 Constant *Op0 = ValueList.getConstantFwdRef(Record[1], OpTy);
2567 Constant *Op1 = ValueList.getConstantFwdRef(Record[2], OpTy);
2568
2569 if (OpTy->isFPOrFPVectorTy())
2570 V = ConstantExpr::getFCmp(Record[3], Op0, Op1);
2571 else
2572 V = ConstantExpr::getICmp(Record[3], Op0, Op1);
2573 break;
2574 }
2575 // This maintains backward compatibility, pre-asm dialect keywords.
2576 // FIXME: Remove with the 4.0 release.
2577 case bitc::CST_CODE_INLINEASM_OLD: {
2578 if (Record.size() < 2)
2579 return error("Invalid record");
2580 std::string AsmStr, ConstrStr;
2581 bool HasSideEffects = Record[0] & 1;
2582 bool IsAlignStack = Record[0] >> 1;
2583 unsigned AsmStrSize = Record[1];
2584 if (2+AsmStrSize >= Record.size())
2585 return error("Invalid record");
2586 unsigned ConstStrSize = Record[2+AsmStrSize];
2587 if (3+AsmStrSize+ConstStrSize > Record.size())
2588 return error("Invalid record");
2589
2590 for (unsigned i = 0; i != AsmStrSize; ++i)
2591 AsmStr += (char)Record[2+i];
2592 for (unsigned i = 0; i != ConstStrSize; ++i)
2593 ConstrStr += (char)Record[3+AsmStrSize+i];
2594 PointerType *PTy = cast<PointerType>(CurTy);
2595 UpgradeInlineAsmString(&AsmStr);
2596 V = InlineAsm::get(cast<FunctionType>(PTy->getElementType()),
2597 AsmStr, ConstrStr, HasSideEffects, IsAlignStack);
2598 break;
2599 }
2600 // This version adds support for the asm dialect keywords (e.g.,
2601 // inteldialect).
2602 case bitc::CST_CODE_INLINEASM: {
2603 if (Record.size() < 2)
2604 return error("Invalid record");
2605 std::string AsmStr, ConstrStr;
2606 bool HasSideEffects = Record[0] & 1;
2607 bool IsAlignStack = (Record[0] >> 1) & 1;
2608 unsigned AsmDialect = Record[0] >> 2;
2609 unsigned AsmStrSize = Record[1];
2610 if (2+AsmStrSize >= Record.size())
2611 return error("Invalid record");
2612 unsigned ConstStrSize = Record[2+AsmStrSize];
2613 if (3+AsmStrSize+ConstStrSize > Record.size())
2614 return error("Invalid record");
2615
2616 for (unsigned i = 0; i != AsmStrSize; ++i)
2617 AsmStr += (char)Record[2+i];
2618 for (unsigned i = 0; i != ConstStrSize; ++i)
2619 ConstrStr += (char)Record[3+AsmStrSize+i];
2620 PointerType *PTy = cast<PointerType>(CurTy);
2621 UpgradeInlineAsmString(&AsmStr);
2622 V = InlineAsm::get(cast<FunctionType>(PTy->getElementType()),
2623 AsmStr, ConstrStr, HasSideEffects, IsAlignStack,
2624 InlineAsm::AsmDialect(AsmDialect));
2625 break;
2626 }
2627 case bitc::CST_CODE_BLOCKADDRESS:{
2628 if (Record.size() < 3)
2629 return error("Invalid record");
2630 Type *FnTy = getTypeByID(Record[0]);
2631 if (!FnTy)
2632 return error("Invalid record");
2633 Function *Fn =
2634 dyn_cast_or_null<Function>(ValueList.getConstantFwdRef(Record[1],FnTy));
2635 if (!Fn)
2636 return error("Invalid record");
2637
2638 // If the function is already parsed we can insert the block address right
2639 // away.
2640 BasicBlock *BB;
2641 unsigned BBID = Record[2];
2642 if (!BBID)
2643 // Invalid reference to entry block.
2644 return error("Invalid ID");
2645 if (!Fn->empty()) {
2646 Function::iterator BBI = Fn->begin(), BBE = Fn->end();
2647 for (size_t I = 0, E = BBID; I != E; ++I) {
2648 if (BBI == BBE)
2649 return error("Invalid ID");
2650 ++BBI;
2651 }
2652 BB = &*BBI;
2653 } else {
2654 // Otherwise insert a placeholder and remember it so it can be inserted
2655 // when the function is parsed.
2656 auto &FwdBBs = BasicBlockFwdRefs[Fn];
2657 if (FwdBBs.empty())
2658 BasicBlockFwdRefQueue.push_back(Fn);
2659 if (FwdBBs.size() < BBID + 1)
2660 FwdBBs.resize(BBID + 1);
2661 if (!FwdBBs[BBID])
2662 FwdBBs[BBID] = BasicBlock::Create(Context);
2663 BB = FwdBBs[BBID];
2664 }
2665 V = BlockAddress::get(Fn, BB);
2666 break;
2667 }
2668 }
2669
2670 ValueList.assignValue(V, NextCstNo);
2671 ++NextCstNo;
2672 }
2673}
2674
2675Error BitcodeReader::parseUseLists() {
2676 if (Stream.EnterSubBlock(bitc::USELIST_BLOCK_ID))
2677 return error("Invalid record");
2678
2679 // Read all the records.
2680 SmallVector<uint64_t, 64> Record;
2681
2682 while (true) {
2683 BitstreamEntry Entry = Stream.advanceSkippingSubblocks();
2684
2685 switch (Entry.Kind) {
2686 case BitstreamEntry::SubBlock: // Handled for us already.
2687 case BitstreamEntry::Error:
2688 return error("Malformed block");
2689 case BitstreamEntry::EndBlock:
2690 return Error::success();
2691 case BitstreamEntry::Record:
2692 // The interesting case.
2693 break;
2694 }
2695
2696 // Read a use list record.
2697 Record.clear();
2698 bool IsBB = false;
2699 switch (Stream.readRecord(Entry.ID, Record)) {
2700 default: // Default behavior: unknown type.
2701 break;
2702 case bitc::USELIST_CODE_BB:
2703 IsBB = true;
2704 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
2705 case bitc::USELIST_CODE_DEFAULT: {
2706 unsigned RecordLength = Record.size();
2707 if (RecordLength < 3)
2708 // Records should have at least an ID and two indexes.
2709 return error("Invalid record");
2710 unsigned ID = Record.back();
2711 Record.pop_back();
2712
2713 Value *V;
2714 if (IsBB) {
2715 assert(ID < FunctionBBs.size() && "Basic block not found");
2716 V = FunctionBBs[ID];
2717 } else
2718 V = ValueList[ID];
2719 unsigned NumUses = 0;
2720 SmallDenseMap<const Use *, unsigned, 16> Order;
2721 for (const Use &U : V->materialized_uses()) {
2722 if (++NumUses > Record.size())
2723 break;
2724 Order[&U] = Record[NumUses - 1];
2725 }
2726 if (Order.size() != Record.size() || NumUses > Record.size())
2727 // Mismatches can happen if the functions are being materialized lazily
2728 // (out-of-order), or a value has been upgraded.
2729 break;
2730
2731 V->sortUseList([&](const Use &L, const Use &R) {
2732 return Order.lookup(&L) < Order.lookup(&R);
2733 });
2734 break;
2735 }
2736 }
2737 }
2738}
2739
2740/// When we see the block for metadata, remember where it is and then skip it.
2741/// This lets us lazily deserialize the metadata.
2742Error BitcodeReader::rememberAndSkipMetadata() {
2743 // Save the current stream state.
2744 uint64_t CurBit = Stream.GetCurrentBitNo();
2745 DeferredMetadataInfo.push_back(CurBit);
2746
2747 // Skip over the block for now.
2748 if (Stream.SkipBlock())
2749 return error("Invalid record");
2750 return Error::success();
2751}
2752
2753Error BitcodeReader::materializeMetadata() {
2754 for (uint64_t BitPos : DeferredMetadataInfo) {
2755 // Move the bit stream to the saved position.
2756 Stream.JumpToBit(BitPos);
2757 if (Error Err = MDLoader->parseModuleMetadata())
2758 return Err;
2759 }
2760
2761 // Upgrade "Linker Options" module flag to "llvm.linker.options" module-level
2762 // metadata.
2763 if (Metadata *Val = TheModule->getModuleFlag("Linker Options")) {
2764 NamedMDNode *LinkerOpts =
2765 TheModule->getOrInsertNamedMetadata("llvm.linker.options");
2766 for (const MDOperand &MDOptions : cast<MDNode>(Val)->operands())
2767 LinkerOpts->addOperand(cast<MDNode>(MDOptions));
2768 }
2769
2770 DeferredMetadataInfo.clear();
2771 return Error::success();
2772}
2773
2774void BitcodeReader::setStripDebugInfo() { StripDebugInfo = true; }
2775
2776/// When we see the block for a function body, remember where it is and then
2777/// skip it. This lets us lazily deserialize the functions.
2778Error BitcodeReader::rememberAndSkipFunctionBody() {
2779 // Get the function we are talking about.
2780 if (FunctionsWithBodies.empty())
2781 return error("Insufficient function protos");
2782
2783 Function *Fn = FunctionsWithBodies.back();
2784 FunctionsWithBodies.pop_back();
2785
2786 // Save the current stream state.
2787 uint64_t CurBit = Stream.GetCurrentBitNo();
2788 assert(
2789 (DeferredFunctionInfo[Fn] == 0 || DeferredFunctionInfo[Fn] == CurBit) &&
2790 "Mismatch between VST and scanned function offsets");
2791 DeferredFunctionInfo[Fn] = CurBit;
2792
2793 // Skip over the function block for now.
2794 if (Stream.SkipBlock())
2795 return error("Invalid record");
2796 return Error::success();
2797}
2798
2799Error BitcodeReader::globalCleanup() {
2800 // Patch the initializers for globals and aliases up.
2801 if (Error Err = resolveGlobalAndIndirectSymbolInits())
2802 return Err;
2803 if (!GlobalInits.empty() || !IndirectSymbolInits.empty())
2804 return error("Malformed global initializer set");
2805
2806 // Look for intrinsic functions which need to be upgraded at some point
2807 for (Function &F : *TheModule) {
2808 MDLoader->upgradeDebugIntrinsics(F);
2809 Function *NewFn;
2810 if (UpgradeIntrinsicFunction(&F, NewFn))
2811 UpgradedIntrinsics[&F] = NewFn;
2812 else if (auto Remangled = Intrinsic::remangleIntrinsicFunction(&F))
2813 // Some types could be renamed during loading if several modules are
2814 // loaded in the same LLVMContext (LTO scenario). In this case we should
2815 // remangle intrinsics names as well.
2816 RemangledIntrinsics[&F] = Remangled.getValue();
2817 }
2818
2819 // Look for global variables which need to be renamed.
2820 std::vector<std::pair<GlobalVariable *, GlobalVariable *>> UpgradedVariables;
2821 for (GlobalVariable &GV : TheModule->globals())
2822 if (GlobalVariable *Upgraded = UpgradeGlobalVariable(&GV))
2823 UpgradedVariables.emplace_back(&GV, Upgraded);
2824 for (auto &Pair : UpgradedVariables) {
2825 Pair.first->eraseFromParent();
2826 TheModule->getGlobalList().push_back(Pair.second);
2827 }
2828
2829 // Force deallocation of memory for these vectors to favor the client that
2830 // want lazy deserialization.
2831 std::vector<std::pair<GlobalVariable *, unsigned>>().swap(GlobalInits);
2832 std::vector<std::pair<GlobalIndirectSymbol *, unsigned>>().swap(
2833 IndirectSymbolInits);
2834 return Error::success();
2835}
2836
2837/// Support for lazy parsing of function bodies. This is required if we
2838/// either have an old bitcode file without a VST forward declaration record,
2839/// or if we have an anonymous function being materialized, since anonymous
2840/// functions do not have a name and are therefore not in the VST.
2841Error BitcodeReader::rememberAndSkipFunctionBodies() {
2842 Stream.JumpToBit(NextUnreadBit);
2843
2844 if (Stream.AtEndOfStream())
2845 return error("Could not find function in stream");
2846
2847 if (!SeenFirstFunctionBody)
2848 return error("Trying to materialize functions before seeing function blocks");
2849
2850 // An old bitcode file with the symbol table at the end would have
2851 // finished the parse greedily.
2852 assert(SeenValueSymbolTable);
2853
2854 SmallVector<uint64_t, 64> Record;
2855
2856 while (true) {
2857 BitstreamEntry Entry = Stream.advance();
2858 switch (Entry.Kind) {
2859 default:
2860 return error("Expect SubBlock");
2861 case BitstreamEntry::SubBlock:
2862 switch (Entry.ID) {
2863 default:
2864 return error("Expect function block");
2865 case bitc::FUNCTION_BLOCK_ID:
2866 if (Error Err = rememberAndSkipFunctionBody())
2867 return Err;
2868 NextUnreadBit = Stream.GetCurrentBitNo();
2869 return Error::success();
2870 }
2871 }
2872 }
2873}

2875bool BitcodeReaderBase::readBlockInfo() {
2876 Optional<BitstreamBlockInfo> NewBlockInfo = Stream.ReadBlockInfoBlock();
2877 if (!NewBlockInfo)
2878 return true;
2879 BlockInfo = std::move(*NewBlockInfo);
2880 return false;
2881}

2883Error BitcodeReader::parseComdatRecord(ArrayRef<uint64_t> Record) {
2884 // v1: [selection_kind, name]
2885 // v2: [strtab_offset, strtab_size, selection_kind]
2886 StringRef Name;
2887 std::tie(Name, Record) = readNameFromStrtab(Record);
2888
2889 if (Record.empty())
2890 return error("Invalid record");
2891 Comdat::SelectionKind SK = getDecodedComdatSelectionKind(Record[0]);
2892 std::string OldFormatName;
2893 if (!UseStrtab) {
2894 if (Record.size() < 2)
2895 return error("Invalid record");
2896 unsigned ComdatNameSize = Record[1];
2897 OldFormatName.reserve(ComdatNameSize);
2898 for (unsigned i = 0; i != ComdatNameSize; ++i)
2899 OldFormatName += (char)Record[2 + i];
2900 Name = OldFormatName;
2901 }
2902 Comdat *C = TheModule->getOrInsertComdat(Name);
2903 C->setSelectionKind(SK);
2904 ComdatList.push_back(C);
2905 return Error::success();
2906}

2908static void inferDSOLocal(GlobalValue *GV) {
2909 // infer dso_local from linkage and visibility if it is not encoded.
2910 if (GV->hasLocalLinkage() ||
2911 (!GV->hasDefaultVisibility() && !GV->hasExternalWeakLinkage()))
2912 GV->setDSOLocal(true);
2913}
2914
2915Error BitcodeReader::parseGlobalVarRecord(ArrayRef<uint64_t> Record) {
2916 // v1: [pointer type, isconst, initid, linkage, alignment, section,
2917 // visibility, threadlocal, unnamed_addr, externally_initialized,
2918 // dllstorageclass, comdat, attributes, preemption specifier,
2919 // partition strtab offset, partition strtab size] (name in VST)
2920 // v2: [strtab_offset, strtab_size, v1]
2921 StringRef Name;
2922 std::tie(Name, Record) = readNameFromStrtab(Record);
2923
2924 if (Record.size() < 6)
2925 return error("Invalid record");
2926 Type *Ty = getTypeByID(Record[0]);
2927 if (!Ty)
2928 return error("Invalid record");
2929 bool isConstant = Record[1] & 1;
2930 bool explicitType = Record[1] & 2;
2931 unsigned AddressSpace;
2932 if (explicitType) {
2933 AddressSpace = Record[1] >> 2;
2934 } else {
2935 if (!Ty->isPointerTy())
2936 return error("Invalid type for value");
2937 AddressSpace = cast<PointerType>(Ty)->getAddressSpace();
2938 Ty = cast<PointerType>(Ty)->getElementType();
2939 }
2940
2941 uint64_t RawLinkage = Record[3];
2942 GlobalValue::LinkageTypes Linkage = getDecodedLinkage(RawLinkage);
2943 unsigned Alignment;
2944 if (Error Err = parseAlignmentValue(Record[4], Alignment))
2945 return Err;
2946 std::string Section;
2947 if (Record[5]) {
2948 if (Record[5] - 1 >= SectionTable.size())
2949 return error("Invalid ID");
2950 Section = SectionTable[Record[5] - 1];
2951 }
2952 GlobalValue::VisibilityTypes Visibility = GlobalValue::DefaultVisibility;
2953 // Local linkage must have default visibility.
2954 if (Record.size() > 6 && !GlobalValue::isLocalLinkage(Linkage))
2955 // FIXME: Change to an error if non-default in 4.0.
2956 Visibility = getDecodedVisibility(Record[6]);
2957
2958 GlobalVariable::ThreadLocalMode TLM = GlobalVariable::NotThreadLocal;
2959 if (Record.size() > 7)
2960 TLM = getDecodedThreadLocalMode(Record[7]);
2961
2962 GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr UnnamedAddr = GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::None;
2963 if (Record.size() > 8)
2964 UnnamedAddr = getDecodedUnnamedAddrType(Record[8]);
2965
2966 bool ExternallyInitialized = false;
2967 if (Record.size() > 9)
2968 ExternallyInitialized = Record[9];
2969
2970 GlobalVariable *NewGV =
2971 new GlobalVariable(*TheModule, Ty, isConstant, Linkage, nullptr, Name,
2972 nullptr, TLM, AddressSpace, ExternallyInitialized);
2973 NewGV->setAlignment(Alignment);
2974 if (!Section.empty())
2975 NewGV->setSection(Section);
2976 NewGV->setVisibility(Visibility);
2977 NewGV->setUnnamedAddr(UnnamedAddr);
2978
2979 if (Record.size() > 10)
2980 NewGV->setDLLStorageClass(getDecodedDLLStorageClass(Record[10]));
2981 else
2982 upgradeDLLImportExportLinkage(NewGV, RawLinkage);
2983
2984 ValueList.push_back(NewGV);
2985
2986 // Remember which value to use for the global initializer.
2987 if (unsigned InitID = Record[2])
2988 GlobalInits.push_back(std::make_pair(NewGV, InitID - 1));
2989
2990 if (Record.size() > 11) {
2991 if (unsigned ComdatID = Record[11]) {
2992 if (ComdatID > ComdatList.size())
2993 return error("Invalid global variable comdat ID");
2994 NewGV->setComdat(ComdatList[ComdatID - 1]);
2995 }
2996 } else if (hasImplicitComdat(RawLinkage)) {
2997 NewGV->setComdat(reinterpret_cast<Comdat *>(1));
2998 }
2999
3000 if (Record.size() > 12) {
3001 auto AS = getAttributes(Record[12]).getFnAttributes();
3002 NewGV->setAttributes(AS);
3003 }
3004
3005 if (Record.size() > 13) {
3006 NewGV->setDSOLocal(getDecodedDSOLocal(Record[13]));
3007 }
3008 inferDSOLocal(NewGV);
3009
3010 // Check whether we have enough values to read a partition name.
3011 if (Record.size() > 15)
3012 NewGV->setPartition(StringRef(Strtab.data() + Record[14], Record[15]));
3013
3014 return Error::success();
3015}
3016
3017Error BitcodeReader::parseFunctionRecord(ArrayRef<uint64_t> Record) {
3018 // v1: [type, callingconv, isproto, linkage, paramattr, alignment, section,
3019 // visibility, gc, unnamed_addr, prologuedata, dllstorageclass, comdat,
3020 // prefixdata, personalityfn, preemption specifier, addrspace] (name in VST)
3021 // v2: [strtab_offset, strtab_size, v1]
3022 StringRef Name;
3023 std::tie(Name, Record) = readNameFromStrtab(Record);
3024
3025 if (Record.size() < 8)
3026 return error("Invalid record");
3027 Type *Ty = getTypeByID(Record[0]);
3028 if (!Ty)
3029 return error("Invalid record");
3030 if (auto *PTy = dyn_cast<PointerType>(Ty))
3031 Ty = PTy->getElementType();
3032 auto *FTy = dyn_cast<FunctionType>(Ty);
3033 if (!FTy)
3034 return error("Invalid type for value");
3035 auto CC = static_cast<CallingConv::ID>(Record[1]);
3036 if (CC & ~CallingConv::MaxID)
3037 return error("Invalid calling convention ID");
3038
3039 unsigned AddrSpace = TheModule->getDataLayout().getProgramAddressSpace();
3040 if (Record.size() > 16)
3041 AddrSpace = Record[16];
3042
3043 Function *Func = Function::Create(FTy, GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage,
3044 AddrSpace, Name, TheModule);
3045
3046 Func->setCallingConv(CC);
3047 bool isProto = Record[2];
3048 uint64_t RawLinkage = Record[3];
3049 Func->setLinkage(getDecodedLinkage(RawLinkage));
3050 Func->setAttributes(getAttributes(Record[4]));
3051
3052 // Upgrade any old-style byval without a type by propagating the argument's
3053 // pointee type. There should be no opaque pointers where the byval type is
3054 // implicit.
3055 for (auto &Arg : Func->args()) {
3056 if (Arg.hasByValAttr() &&
3057 !Arg.getAttribute(Attribute::ByVal).getValueAsType()) {
3058 Arg.removeAttr(Attribute::ByVal);
3059 Arg.addAttr(Attribute::getWithByValType(
3060 Context, Arg.getType()->getPointerElementType()));
3061 }
3062 }
3063
3064 unsigned Alignment;
3065 if (Error Err = parseAlignmentValue(Record[5], Alignment))
3066 return Err;
3067 Func->setAlignment(Alignment);
3068 if (Record[6]) {
3069 if (Record[6] - 1 >= SectionTable.size())
3070 return error("Invalid ID");
3071 Func->setSection(SectionTable[Record[6] - 1]);
3072 }
3073 // Local linkage must have default visibility.
3074 if (!Func->hasLocalLinkage())
3075 // FIXME: Change to an error if non-default in 4.0.
3076 Func->setVisibility(getDecodedVisibility(Record[7]));
3077 if (Record.size() > 8 && Record[8]) {
3078 if (Record[8] - 1 >= GCTable.size())
3079 return error("Invalid ID");
3080 Func->setGC(GCTable[Record[8] - 1]);
3081 }
3082 GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr UnnamedAddr = GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::None;
3083 if (Record.size() > 9)
3084 UnnamedAddr = getDecodedUnnamedAddrType(Record[9]);
3085 Func->setUnnamedAddr(UnnamedAddr);
3086 if (Record.size() > 10 && Record[10] != 0)
3087 FunctionPrologues.push_back(std::make_pair(Func, Record[10] - 1));
3088
3089 if (Record.size() > 11)
3090 Func->setDLLStorageClass(getDecodedDLLStorageClass(Record[11]));
3091 else
3092 upgradeDLLImportExportLinkage(Func, RawLinkage);
3093
3094 if (Record.size() > 12) {
3095 if (unsigned ComdatID = Record[12]) {
3096 if (ComdatID > ComdatList.size())
3097 return error("Invalid function comdat ID");
3098 Func->setComdat(ComdatList[ComdatID - 1]);
3099 }
3100 } else if (hasImplicitComdat(RawLinkage)) {
3101 Func->setComdat(reinterpret_cast<Comdat *>(1));
3102 }
3103
3104 if (Record.size() > 13 && Record[13] != 0)
3105 FunctionPrefixes.push_back(std::make_pair(Func, Record[13] - 1));
3106
3107 if (Record.size() > 14 && Record[14] != 0)
3108 FunctionPersonalityFns.push_back(std::make_pair(Func, Record[14] - 1));
3109
3110 if (Record.size() > 15) {
3111 Func->setDSOLocal(getDecodedDSOLocal(Record[15]));
3112 }
3113 inferDSOLocal(Func);
3114
3115 // Record[16] is the address space number.
3116
3117 // Check whether we have enough values to read a partition name.
3118 if (Record.size() > 18)
3119 Func->setPartition(StringRef(Strtab.data() + Record[17], Record[18]));
3120
3121 ValueList.push_back(Func);
3122
3123 // If this is a function with a body, remember the prototype we are
3124 // creating now, so that we can match up the body with them later.
3125 if (!isProto) {
3126 Func->setIsMaterializable(true);
3127 FunctionsWithBodies.push_back(Func);
3128 DeferredFunctionInfo[Func] = 0;
3129 }
3130 return Error::success();
3131}
3132
3133Error BitcodeReader::parseGlobalIndirectSymbolRecord(
3134 unsigned BitCode, ArrayRef<uint64_t> Record) {
3135 // v1 ALIAS_OLD: [alias type, aliasee val#, linkage] (name in VST)
3136 // v1 ALIAS: [alias type, addrspace, aliasee val#, linkage, visibility,
3137 // dllstorageclass, threadlocal, unnamed_addr,
3138 // preemption specifier] (name in VST)
3139 // v1 IFUNC: [alias type, addrspace, aliasee val#, linkage,
3140 // visibility, dllstorageclass, threadlocal, unnamed_addr,
3141 // preemption specifier] (name in VST)
3142 // v2: [strtab_offset, strtab_size, v1]
3143 StringRef Name;
3144 std::tie(Name, Record) = readNameFromStrtab(Record);
3145
3146 bool NewRecord = BitCode != bitc::MODULE_CODE_ALIAS_OLD;
3147 if (Record.size() < (3 + (unsigned)NewRecord))
3148 return error("Invalid record");
3149 unsigned OpNum = 0;
3150 Type *Ty = getTypeByID(Record[OpNum++]);
3151 if (!Ty)
3152 return error("Invalid record");
3153
3154 unsigned AddrSpace;
3155 if (!NewRecord) {
3156 auto *PTy = dyn_cast<PointerType>(Ty);
3157 if (!PTy)
3158 return error("Invalid type for value");
3159 Ty = PTy->getElementType();
3160 AddrSpace = PTy->getAddressSpace();
3161 } else {
3162 AddrSpace = Record[OpNum++];
3163 }
3164
3165 auto Val = Record[OpNum++];
3166 auto Linkage = Record[OpNum++];
3167 GlobalIndirectSymbol *NewGA;
3168 if (BitCode == bitc::MODULE_CODE_ALIAS ||
3169 BitCode == bitc::MODULE_CODE_ALIAS_OLD)
3170 NewGA = GlobalAlias::create(Ty, AddrSpace, getDecodedLinkage(Linkage), Name,
3171 TheModule);
3172 else
3173 NewGA = GlobalIFunc::create(Ty, AddrSpace, getDecodedLinkage(Linkage), Name,
3174 nullptr, TheModule);
3175 // Old bitcode files didn't have visibility field.
3176 // Local linkage must have default visibility.
3177 if (OpNum != Record.size()) {
3178 auto VisInd = OpNum++;
3179 if (!NewGA->hasLocalLinkage())
3180 // FIXME: Change to an error if non-default in 4.0.
3181 NewGA->setVisibility(getDecodedVisibility(Record[VisInd]));
3182 }
3183 if (BitCode == bitc::MODULE_CODE_ALIAS ||
3184 BitCode == bitc::MODULE_CODE_ALIAS_OLD) {
3185 if (OpNum != Record.size())
3186 NewGA->setDLLStorageClass(getDecodedDLLStorageClass(Record[OpNum++]));
3187 else
3188 upgradeDLLImportExportLinkage(NewGA, Linkage);
3189 if (OpNum != Record.size())
3190 NewGA->setThreadLocalMode(getDecodedThreadLocalMode(Record[OpNum++]));
3191 if (OpNum != Record.size())
3192 NewGA->setUnnamedAddr(getDecodedUnnamedAddrType(Record[OpNum++]));
3193 }
3194 if (OpNum != Record.size())
3195 NewGA->setDSOLocal(getDecodedDSOLocal(Record[OpNum++]));
3196 inferDSOLocal(NewGA);
3197
3198 // Check whether we have enough values to read a partition name.
3199 if (OpNum + 1 < Record.size()) {
3200 NewGA->setPartition(
3201 StringRef(Strtab.data() + Record[OpNum], Record[OpNum + 1]));
3202 OpNum += 2;
3203 }
3204
3205 ValueList.push_back(NewGA);
3206 IndirectSymbolInits.push_back(std::make_pair(NewGA, Val));
3207 return Error::success();
3208}
3209
3210Error BitcodeReader::parseModule(uint64_t ResumeBit,
3211 bool ShouldLazyLoadMetadata) {
3212 if (ResumeBit)
3213 Stream.JumpToBit(ResumeBit);
3214 else if (Stream.EnterSubBlock(bitc::MODULE_BLOCK_ID))
3215 return error("Invalid record");
3216
3217 SmallVector<uint64_t, 64> Record;
3218
3219 // Read all the records for this module.
3220 while (true) {
3221 BitstreamEntry Entry = Stream.advance();
3222
3223 switch (Entry.Kind) {
3224 case BitstreamEntry::Error:
3225 return error("Malformed block");
3226 case BitstreamEntry::EndBlock:
3227 return globalCleanup();
3228
3229 case BitstreamEntry::SubBlock:
3230 switch (Entry.ID) {
3231 default: // Skip unknown content.
3232 if (Stream.SkipBlock())
3233 return error("Invalid record");
3234 break;
3235 case bitc::BLOCKINFO_BLOCK_ID:
3236 if (readBlockInfo())
3237 return error("Malformed block");
3238 break;
3239 case bitc::PARAMATTR_BLOCK_ID:
3240 if (Error Err = parseAttributeBlock())
3241 return Err;
3242 break;
3243 case bitc::PARAMATTR_GROUP_BLOCK_ID:
3244 if (Error Err = parseAttributeGroupBlock())
3245 return Err;
3246 break;
3247 case bitc::TYPE_BLOCK_ID_NEW:
3248 if (Error Err = parseTypeTable())
3249 return Err;
3250 break;
3251 case bitc::VALUE_SYMTAB_BLOCK_ID:
3252 if (!SeenValueSymbolTable) {
3253 // Either this is an old form VST without function index and an
3254 // associated VST forward declaration record (which would have caused
3255 // the VST to be jumped to and parsed before it was encountered
3256 // normally in the stream), or there were no function blocks to
3257 // trigger an earlier parsing of the VST.
3258 assert(VSTOffset == 0 || FunctionsWithBodies.empty());
3259 if (Error Err = parseValueSymbolTable())
3260 return Err;
3261 SeenValueSymbolTable = true;
3262 } else {
3263 // We must have had a VST forward declaration record, which caused
3264 // the parser to jump to and parse the VST earlier.
3265 assert(VSTOffset > 0);
3266 if (Stream.SkipBlock())
3267 return error("Invalid record");
3268 }
3269 break;
3270 case bitc::CONSTANTS_BLOCK_ID:
3271 if (Error Err = parseConstants())
3272 return Err;
3273 if (Error Err = resolveGlobalAndIndirectSymbolInits())
3274 return Err;
3275 break;
3276 case bitc::METADATA_BLOCK_ID:
3277 if (ShouldLazyLoadMetadata) {
3278 if (Error Err = rememberAndSkipMetadata())
3279 return Err;
3280 break;
3281 }
3282 assert(DeferredMetadataInfo.empty() && "Unexpected deferred metadata");
3283 if (Error Err = MDLoader->parseModuleMetadata())
3284 return Err;
3285 break;
3286 case bitc::METADATA_KIND_BLOCK_ID:
3287 if (Error Err = MDLoader->parseMetadataKinds())
3288 return Err;
3289 break;
3290 case bitc::FUNCTION_BLOCK_ID:
3291 // If this is the first function body we've seen, reverse the
3292 // FunctionsWithBodies list.
3293 if (!SeenFirstFunctionBody) {
3294 std::reverse(FunctionsWithBodies.begin(), FunctionsWithBodies.end());
3295 if (Error Err = globalCleanup())
3296 return Err;
3297 SeenFirstFunctionBody = true;
3298 }
3299
3300 if (VSTOffset > 0) {
3301 // If we have a VST forward declaration record, make sure we
3302 // parse the VST now if we haven't already. It is needed to
3303 // set up the DeferredFunctionInfo vector for lazy reading.
3304 if (!SeenValueSymbolTable) {
3305 if (Error Err = BitcodeReader::parseValueSymbolTable(VSTOffset))
3306 return Err;
3307 SeenValueSymbolTable = true;
3308 // Fall through so that we record the NextUnreadBit below.
3309 // This is necessary in case we have an anonymous function that
3310 // is later materialized. Since it will not have a VST entry we
3311 // need to fall back to the lazy parse to find its offset.
3312 } else {
3313 // If we have a VST forward declaration record, but have already
3314 // parsed the VST (just above, when the first function body was
3315 // encountered here), then we are resuming the parse after
3316 // materializing functions. The ResumeBit points to the
3317 // start of the last function block recorded in the
3318 // DeferredFunctionInfo map. Skip it.
3319 if (Stream.SkipBlock())
3320 return error("Invalid record");
3321 continue;
3322 }
3323 }
3324
3325 // Support older bitcode files that did not have the function
3326 // index in the VST, nor a VST forward declaration record, as
3327 // well as anonymous functions that do not have VST entries.
3328 // Build the DeferredFunctionInfo vector on the fly.
3329 if (Error Err = rememberAndSkipFunctionBody())
3330 return Err;
3331
3332 // Suspend parsing when we reach the function bodies. Subsequent
3333 // materialization calls will resume it when necessary. If the bitcode
3334 // file is old, the symbol table will be at the end instead and will not
3335 // have been seen yet. In this case, just finish the parse now.
3336 if (SeenValueSymbolTable) {
3337 NextUnreadBit = Stream.GetCurrentBitNo();
3338 // After the VST has been parsed, we need to make sure intrinsic name
3339 // are auto-upgraded.
3340 return globalCleanup();
3341 }
3342 break;
3343 case bitc::USELIST_BLOCK_ID:
3344 if (Error Err = parseUseLists())
3345 return Err;
3346 break;
3347 case bitc::OPERAND_BUNDLE_TAGS_BLOCK_ID:
3348 if (Error Err = parseOperandBundleTags())
3349 return Err;
3350 break;
3351 case bitc::SYNC_SCOPE_NAMES_BLOCK_ID:
3352 if (Error Err = parseSyncScopeNames())
3353 return Err;
3354 break;
3355 }
3356 continue;
3357
3358 case BitstreamEntry::Record:
3359 // The interesting case.
3360 break;
3361 }
3362
3363 // Read a record.
3364 auto BitCode = Stream.readRecord(Entry.ID, Record);
3365 switch (BitCode) {
3366 default: break; // Default behavior, ignore unknown content.
3367 case bitc::MODULE_CODE_VERSION: {
3368 Expected<unsigned> VersionOrErr = parseVersionRecord(Record);
3369 if (!VersionOrErr)
3370 return VersionOrErr.takeError();
3371 UseRelativeIDs = *VersionOrErr >= 1;
3372 break;
3373 }
3374 case bitc::MODULE_CODE_TRIPLE: { // TRIPLE: [strchr x N]
3375 std::string S;
3376 if (convertToString(Record, 0, S))
3377 return error("Invalid record");
3378 TheModule->setTargetTriple(S);
3379 break;
3380 }
3381 case bitc::MODULE_CODE_DATALAYOUT: { // DATALAYOUT: [strchr x N]
3382 std::string S;
3383 if (convertToString(Record, 0, S))
3384 return error("Invalid record");
3385 TheModule->setDataLayout(S);
3386 break;
3387 }
3388 case bitc::MODULE_CODE_ASM: { // ASM: [strchr x N]
3389 std::string S;
3390 if (convertToString(Record, 0, S))
3391 return error("Invalid record");
3392 TheModule->setModuleInlineAsm(S);
3393 break;
3394 }
3395 case bitc::MODULE_CODE_DEPLIB: { // DEPLIB: [strchr x N]
3396 // FIXME: Remove in 4.0.
3397 std::string S;
3398 if (convertToString(Record, 0, S))
3399 return error("Invalid record");
3400 // Ignore value.
3401 break;
3402 }
3403 case bitc::MODULE_CODE_SECTIONNAME: { // SECTIONNAME: [strchr x N]
3404 std::string S;
3405 if (convertToString(Record, 0, S))
3406 return error("Invalid record");
3407 SectionTable.push_back(S);
3408 break;
3409 }
3410 case bitc::MODULE_CODE_GCNAME: { // SECTIONNAME: [strchr x N]
3411 std::string S;
3412 if (convertToString(Record, 0, S))
3413 return error("Invalid record");
3414 GCTable.push_back(S);
3415 break;
3416 }
3417 case bitc::MODULE_CODE_COMDAT:
3418 if (Error Err = parseComdatRecord(Record))
3419 return Err;
3420 break;
3421 case bitc::MODULE_CODE_GLOBALVAR:
3422 if (Error Err = parseGlobalVarRecord(Record))
3423 return Err;
3424 break;
3425 case bitc::MODULE_CODE_FUNCTION:
3426 if (Error Err = parseFunctionRecord(Record))
3427 return Err;
3428 break;
3429 case bitc::MODULE_CODE_IFUNC:
3430 case bitc::MODULE_CODE_ALIAS:
3431 case bitc::MODULE_CODE_ALIAS_OLD:
3432 if (Error Err = parseGlobalIndirectSymbolRecord(BitCode, Record))
3433 return Err;
3434 break;
3435 /// MODULE_CODE_VSTOFFSET: [offset]
3436 case bitc::MODULE_CODE_VSTOFFSET:
3437 if (Record.size() < 1)
3438 return error("Invalid record");
3439 // Note that we subtract 1 here because the offset is relative to one word
3440 // before the start of the identification or module block, which was
3441 // historically always the start of the regular bitcode header.
3442 VSTOffset = Record[0] - 1;
3443 break;
3444 /// MODULE_CODE_SOURCE_FILENAME: [namechar x N]
3445 case bitc::MODULE_CODE_SOURCE_FILENAME:
3446 SmallString<128> ValueName;
3447 if (convertToString(Record, 0, ValueName))
3448 return error("Invalid record");
3449 TheModule->setSourceFileName(ValueName);
3450 break;
3451 }
3452 Record.clear();
3453 }
3454}
3455
3456Error BitcodeReader::parseBitcodeInto(Module *M, bool ShouldLazyLoadMetadata,
3457 bool IsImporting) {
3458 TheModule = M;
3459 MDLoader = MetadataLoader(Stream, *M, ValueList, IsImporting,
3460 [&](unsigned ID) { return getTypeByID(ID); });
3461 return parseModule(0, ShouldLazyLoadMetadata);
3462}
3463
3464Error BitcodeReader::typeCheckLoadStoreInst(Type *ValType, Type *PtrType) {
3465 if (!isa<PointerType>(PtrType))
3466 return error("Load/Store operand is not a pointer type");
3467 Type *ElemType = cast<PointerType>(PtrType)->getElementType();
3468
3469 if (ValType && ValType != ElemType)
3470 return error("Explicit load/store type does not match pointee "
3471 "type of pointer operand");
3472 if (!PointerType::isLoadableOrStorableType(ElemType))
3473 return error("Cannot load/store from pointer");
3474 return Error::success();
3475}

3477void BitcodeReader::propagateByValTypes(CallBase *CB) {
3478 for (unsigned i = 0; i < CB->getNumArgOperands(); ++i) {
3479 if (CB->paramHasAttr(i, Attribute::ByVal) &&
3480 !CB->getAttribute(i, Attribute::ByVal).getValueAsType()) {
3481 CB->removeParamAttr(i, Attribute::ByVal);
3482 CB->addParamAttr(
3483 i, Attribute::getWithByValType(
3484 Context,
3485 CB->getArgOperand(i)->getType()->getPointerElementType()));
3486 }
3487 }
3488}
3489
3490/// Lazily parse the specified function body block.
3491Error BitcodeReader::parseFunctionBody(Function *F) {
3492 if (Stream.EnterSubBlock(bitc::FUNCTION_BLOCK_ID))
3493 return error("Invalid record");
3494
3495 // Unexpected unresolved metadata when parsing function.
3496 if (MDLoader->hasFwdRefs())
3497 return error("Invalid function metadata: incoming forward references");
3498
3499 InstructionList.clear();
3500 unsigned ModuleValueListSize = ValueList.size();
3501 unsigned ModuleMDLoaderSize = MDLoader->size();
3502
3503 // Add all the function arguments to the value table.
3504 for (Argument &I : F->args())
3505 ValueList.push_back(&I);
3506
3507 unsigned NextValueNo = ValueList.size();
3508 BasicBlock *CurBB = nullptr;
3509 unsigned CurBBNo = 0;
3510
3511 DebugLoc LastLoc;
3512 auto getLastInstruction = [&]() -> Instruction * {
3513 if (CurBB && !CurBB->empty())
3514 return &CurBB->back();
3515 else if (CurBBNo && FunctionBBs[CurBBNo - 1] &&
3516 !FunctionBBs[CurBBNo - 1]->empty())
3517 return &FunctionBBs[CurBBNo - 1]->back();
3518 return nullptr;
3519 };
3520
3521 std::vector<OperandBundleDef> OperandBundles;
3522
3523 // Read all the records.
3524 SmallVector<uint64_t, 64> Record;
3525
3526 while (true) {
3527 BitstreamEntry Entry = Stream.advance();
3528
3529 switch (Entry.Kind) {
3530 case BitstreamEntry::Error:
3531 return error("Malformed block");
3532 case BitstreamEntry::EndBlock:
3533 goto OutOfRecordLoop;
3534
3535 case BitstreamEntry::SubBlock:
3536 switch (Entry.ID) {
3537 default: // Skip unknown content.
3538 if (Stream.SkipBlock())
3539 return error("Invalid record");
3540 break;
3541 case bitc::CONSTANTS_BLOCK_ID:
3542 if (Error Err = parseConstants())
3543 return Err;
3544 NextValueNo = ValueList.size();
3545 break;
3546 case bitc::VALUE_SYMTAB_BLOCK_ID:
3547 if (Error Err = parseValueSymbolTable())
3548 return Err;
3549 break;
3550 case bitc::METADATA_ATTACHMENT_ID:
3551 if (Error Err = MDLoader->parseMetadataAttachment(*F, InstructionList))
3552 return Err;
3553 break;
3554 case bitc::METADATA_BLOCK_ID:
3555 assert(DeferredMetadataInfo.empty() &&
3556 "Must read all module-level metadata before function-level");
3557 if (Error Err = MDLoader->parseFunctionMetadata())
3558 return Err;
3559 break;
3560 case bitc::USELIST_BLOCK_ID:
3561 if (Error Err = parseUseLists())
3562 return Err;
3563 break;
3564 }
3565 continue;
3566
3567 case BitstreamEntry::Record:
3568 // The interesting case.
3569 break;
3570 }
3571
3572 // Read a record.
3573 Record.clear();
3574 Instruction *I = nullptr;
3575 unsigned BitCode = Stream.readRecord(Entry.ID, Record);
3576 switch (BitCode) {
3577 default: // Default behavior: reject
3578 return error("Invalid value");
3579 case bitc::FUNC_CODE_DECLAREBLOCKS: { // DECLAREBLOCKS: [nblocks]
3580 if (Record.size() < 1 || Record[0] == 0)
3581 return error("Invalid record");
3582 // Create all the basic blocks for the function.
3583 FunctionBBs.resize(Record[0]);
3584
3585 // See if anything took the address of blocks in this function.
3586 auto BBFRI = BasicBlockFwdRefs.find(F);
3587 if (BBFRI == BasicBlockFwdRefs.end()) {
3588 for (unsigned i = 0, e = FunctionBBs.size(); i != e; ++i)
3589 FunctionBBs[i] = BasicBlock::Create(Context, "", F);
3590 } else {
3591 auto &BBRefs = BBFRI->second;
3592 // Check for invalid basic block references.
3593 if (BBRefs.size() > FunctionBBs.size())
3594 return error("Invalid ID");
3595 assert(!BBRefs.empty() && "Unexpected empty array");
3596 assert(!BBRefs.front() && "Invalid reference to entry block");
3597 for (unsigned I = 0, E = FunctionBBs.size(), RE = BBRefs.size(); I != E;
3598 ++I)
3599 if (I < RE && BBRefs[I]) {
3600 BBRefs[I]->insertInto(F);
3601 FunctionBBs[I] = BBRefs[I];
3602 } else {
3603 FunctionBBs[I] = BasicBlock::Create(Context, "", F);
3604 }
3605
3606 // Erase from the table.
3607 BasicBlockFwdRefs.erase(BBFRI);
3608 }
3609
3610 CurBB = FunctionBBs[0];
3611 continue;
3612 }
3613
3614 case bitc::FUNC_CODE_DEBUG_LOC_AGAIN: // DEBUG_LOC_AGAIN
3615 // This record indicates that the last instruction is at the same
3616 // location as the previous instruction with a location.
3617 I = getLastInstruction();
3618
3619 if (!I)
3620 return error("Invalid record");
3621 I->setDebugLoc(LastLoc);
3622 I = nullptr;
3623 continue;
3624
3625 case bitc::FUNC_CODE_DEBUG_LOC: { // DEBUG_LOC: [line, col, scope, ia]
3626 I = getLastInstruction();
3627 if (!I || Record.size() < 4)
3628 return error("Invalid record");
3629
3630 unsigned Line = Record[0], Col = Record[1];
3631 unsigned ScopeID = Record[2], IAID = Record[3];
3632 bool isImplicitCode = Record.size() == 5 && Record[4];
3633
3634 MDNode *Scope = nullptr, *IA = nullptr;
3635 if (ScopeID) {
3636 Scope = dyn_cast_or_null<MDNode>(
3637 MDLoader->getMetadataFwdRefOrLoad(ScopeID - 1));
3638 if (!Scope)
3639 return error("Invalid record");
3640 }
3641 if (IAID) {
3642 IA = dyn_cast_or_null<MDNode>(
3643 MDLoader->getMetadataFwdRefOrLoad(IAID - 1));
3644 if (!IA)
3645 return error("Invalid record");
3646 }
3647 LastLoc = DebugLoc::get(Line, Col, Scope, IA, isImplicitCode);
3648 I->setDebugLoc(LastLoc);
3649 I = nullptr;
3650 continue;
3651 }
3652 case bitc::FUNC_CODE_INST_UNOP: { // UNOP: [opval, ty, opcode]
3653 unsigned OpNum = 0;
3654 Value *LHS;
3655 if (getValueTypePair(Record, OpNum, NextValueNo, LHS) ||
3656 OpNum+1 > Record.size())
3657 return error("Invalid record");
3658
3659 int Opc = getDecodedUnaryOpcode(Record[OpNum++], LHS->getType());
3660 if (Opc == -1)
3661 return error("Invalid record");
3662 I = UnaryOperator::Create((Instruction::UnaryOps)Opc, LHS);
3663 InstructionList.push_back(I);
3664 if (OpNum < Record.size()) {
3665 if (isa<FPMathOperator>(I)) {
3666 FastMathFlags FMF = getDecodedFastMathFlags(Record[OpNum]);
3667 if (FMF.any())
3668 I->setFastMathFlags(FMF);
3669 }
3670 }
3671 break;
3672 }
3673 case bitc::FUNC_CODE_INST_BINOP: { // BINOP: [opval, ty, opval, opcode]
3674 unsigned OpNum = 0;
3675 Value *LHS, *RHS;
3676 if (getValueTypePair(Record, OpNum, NextValueNo, LHS) ||
3677 popValue(Record, OpNum, NextValueNo, LHS->getType(), RHS) ||
3678 OpNum+1 > Record.size())
3679 return error("Invalid record");
3680
3681 int Opc = getDecodedBinaryOpcode(Record[OpNum++], LHS->getType());
3682 if (Opc == -1)
3683 return error("Invalid record");
3684 I = BinaryOperator::Create((Instruction::BinaryOps)Opc, LHS, RHS);
3685 InstructionList.push_back(I);
3686 if (OpNum < Record.size()) {
3687 if (Opc == Instruction::Add ||
3688 Opc == Instruction::Sub ||
3689 Opc == Instruction::Mul ||
3690 Opc == Instruction::Shl) {
3691 if (Record[OpNum] & (1 << bitc::OBO_NO_SIGNED_WRAP))
3692 cast<BinaryOperator>(I)->setHasNoSignedWrap(true);
3693 if (Record[OpNum] & (1 << bitc::OBO_NO_UNSIGNED_WRAP))
3694 cast<BinaryOperator>(I)->setHasNoUnsignedWrap(true);
3695 } else if (Opc == Instruction::SDiv ||
3696 Opc == Instruction::UDiv ||
3697 Opc == Instruction::LShr ||
3698 Opc == Instruction::AShr) {
3699 if (Record[OpNum] & (1 << bitc::PEO_EXACT))
3700 cast<BinaryOperator>(I)->setIsExact(true);
3701 } else if (isa<FPMathOperator>(I)) {
3702 FastMathFlags FMF = getDecodedFastMathFlags(Record[OpNum]);
3703 if (FMF.any())
3704 I->setFastMathFlags(FMF);
3705 }
3706
3707 }
3708 break;
3709 }
3710 case bitc::FUNC_CODE_INST_CAST: { // CAST: [opval, opty, destty, castopc]
3711 unsigned OpNum = 0;
3712 Value *Op;
3713 if (getValueTypePair(Record, OpNum, NextValueNo, Op) ||
3714 OpNum+2 != Record.size())
3715 return error("Invalid record");
3716
3717 Type *ResTy = getTypeByID(Record[OpNum]);
3718 int Opc = getDecodedCastOpcode(Record[OpNum + 1]);
3719 if (Opc == -1 || !ResTy)
3720 return error("Invalid record");
3721 Instruction *Temp = nullptr;
3722 if ((I = UpgradeBitCastInst(Opc, Op, ResTy, Temp))) {
3723 if (Temp) {
3724 InstructionList.push_back(Temp);
3725 CurBB->getInstList().push_back(Temp);
3726 }
3727 } else {
3728 auto CastOp = (Instruction::CastOps)Opc;
3729 if (!CastInst::castIsValid(CastOp, Op, ResTy))
3730 return error("Invalid cast");
3731 I = CastInst::Create(CastOp, Op, ResTy);
3732 }
3733 InstructionList.push_back(I);
3734 break;
3735 }
3736 case bitc::FUNC_CODE_INST_INBOUNDS_GEP_OLD:
3737 case bitc::FUNC_CODE_INST_GEP_OLD:
3738 case bitc::FUNC_CODE_INST_GEP: { // GEP: type, [n x operands]
3739 unsigned OpNum = 0;
3740
3741 Type *Ty;
3742 bool InBounds;
3743
3744 if (BitCode == bitc::FUNC_CODE_INST_GEP) {
3745 InBounds = Record[OpNum++];
3746 Ty = getTypeByID(Record[OpNum++]);
3747 } else {
3748 InBounds = BitCode == bitc::FUNC_CODE_INST_INBOUNDS_GEP_OLD;
3749 Ty = nullptr;
3750 }
3751
3752 Value *BasePtr;
3753 if (getValueTypePair(Record, OpNum, NextValueNo, BasePtr))
3754 return error("Invalid record");
3755
3756 if (!Ty)
3757 Ty = cast<PointerType>(BasePtr->getType()->getScalarType())
3758 ->getElementType();
3759 else if (Ty !=
3760 cast<PointerType>(BasePtr->getType()->getScalarType())
3761 ->getElementType())
3762 return error(
3763 "Explicit gep type does not match pointee type of pointer operand");
3764
3765 SmallVector<Value*, 16> GEPIdx;
3766 while (OpNum != Record.size()) {
3767 Value *Op;
3768 if (getValueTypePair(Record, OpNum, NextValueNo, Op))
3769 return error("Invalid record");
3770 GEPIdx.push_back(Op);
3771 }
3772
3773 I = GetElementPtrInst::Create(Ty, BasePtr, GEPIdx);
3774
3775 InstructionList.push_back(I);
3776 if (InBounds)
3777 cast<GetElementPtrInst>(I)->setIsInBounds(true);
3778 break;
3779 }
3780
3781 case bitc::FUNC_CODE_INST_EXTRACTVAL: {
3782 // EXTRACTVAL: [opty, opval, n x indices]
3783 unsigned OpNum = 0;
3784 Value *Agg;
3785 if (getValueTypePair(Record, OpNum, NextValueNo, Agg))
3786 return error("Invalid record");
3787
3788 unsigned RecSize = Record.size();
3789 if (OpNum == RecSize)
3790 return error("EXTRACTVAL: Invalid instruction with 0 indices");
3791
3792 SmallVector<unsigned, 4> EXTRACTVALIdx;
3793 Type *CurTy = Agg->getType();
3794 for (; OpNum != RecSize; ++OpNum) {
3795 bool IsArray = CurTy->isArrayTy();
3796 bool IsStruct = CurTy->isStructTy();
3797 uint64_t Index = Record[OpNum];
3798
3799 if (!IsStruct && !IsArray)
3800 return error("EXTRACTVAL: Invalid type");
3801 if ((unsigned)Index != Index)
3802 return error("Invalid value");
3803 if (IsStruct && Index >= CurTy->getStructNumElements())
3804 return error("EXTRACTVAL: Invalid struct index");
3805 if (IsArray && Index >= CurTy->getArrayNumElements())
3806 return error("EXTRACTVAL: Invalid array index");
3807 EXTRACTVALIdx.push_back((unsigned)Index);
3808
3809 if (IsStruct)
3810 CurTy = CurTy->getStructElementType(Index);
3811 else
3812 CurTy = CurTy->getArrayElementType();
3813 }
3814
3815 I = ExtractValueInst::Create(Agg, EXTRACTVALIdx);
3816 InstructionList.push_back(I);
3817 break;
3818 }
3819
3820 case bitc::FUNC_CODE_INST_INSERTVAL: {
3821 // INSERTVAL: [opty, opval, opty, opval, n x indices]
3822 unsigned OpNum = 0;
3823 Value *Agg;

3827 if (getValueTypePair(Record, OpNum, NextValueNo, Val))

3842 return error("INSERTVAL: Invalid type");

3844 return error("Invalid value");

3846 return error("INSERTVAL: Invalid struct index");
3847 if (IsArray && Index >= CurTy->getArrayNumElements())
3848 return error("INSERTVAL: Invalid array index");

3853 else

4140 // format were reverted but we still recognize bitcode that uses it.

4142 // this format again.

4155 InstructionList.push_back(SI);

4158 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumCases; ++i) {
4159 SmallVector<ConstantInt*, 1> CaseVals;
4160 unsigned NumItems = Record[CurIdx++];
4161 for (unsigned ci = 0; ci != NumItems; ++ci) {

4169 ValueBitWidth);

4173 ActiveWords = 1;

4177 makeArrayRef(&Record[CurIdx], ActiveWords), ValueBitWidth);

4181 // compared as signed or unsigned values. The partially

4185 CaseVals.push_back(ConstantInt::get(Context, Low));
4186 } else
4187 CaseVals.push_back(ConstantInt::get(Context, Low));
4188 }

4191 cve = CaseVals.end(); cvi != cve; ++cvi)

4193 }

4195 break;

4217 }

4221 break;
4222 }

4433 if (BitCode == bitc::FUNC_CODE_INST_LANDINGPAD_OLD) {
4434 Value *PersFn = nullptr;
4435 if (getValueTypePair(Record, Idx, NextValueNo, PersFn))
4436 return error("Invalid record");
4437
4438 if (!F->hasPersonalityFn())
4439 F->setPersonalityFn(cast<Constant>(PersFn));
4440 else if (F->getPersonalityFn() != cast<Constant>(PersFn))
4441 return error("Personality function mismatch");
4442 }
4443
4444 bool IsCleanup = !!Record[Idx++];
4445 unsigned NumClauses = Record[Idx++];
4446 LandingPadInst *LP = LandingPadInst::Create(Ty, NumClauses);
4447 LP->setCleanup(IsCleanup);
4448 for (unsigned J = 0; J != NumClauses; ++J) {
4449 LandingPadInst::ClauseType CT =
4450 LandingPadInst::ClauseType(Record[Idx++]); (void)CT;
4451 Value *Val;
4452
4453 if (getValueTypePair(Record, Idx, NextValueNo, Val)) {
4454 delete LP;
4455 return error("Invalid record");
4456 }
4457
4458 assert((CT != LandingPadInst::Catch ||
4459 !isa<ArrayType>(Val->getType())) &&
4460 "Catch clause has a invalid type!");
4461 assert((CT != LandingPadInst::Filter ||
4462 isa<ArrayType>(Val->getType())) &&
4463 "Filter clause has invalid type!");
4464 LP->addClause(cast<Constant>(Val));
4465 }
4466
4467 I = LP;
4468 InstructionList.push_back(I);
4469 break;
4470 }
4471
4472 case bitc::FUNC_CODE_INST_ALLOCA: { // ALLOCA: [instty, opty, op, align]
4473 if (Record.size() != 4)
4474 return error("Invalid record");
4475 uint64_t AlignRecord = Record[3];
4476 const uint64_t InAllocaMask = uint64_t(1) << 5;
4477 const uint64_t ExplicitTypeMask = uint64_t(1) << 6;
4478 const uint64_t SwiftErrorMask = uint64_t(1) << 7;
4479 const uint64_t FlagMask = InAllocaMask | ExplicitTypeMask |
4480 SwiftErrorMask;
4481 bool InAlloca = AlignRecord & InAllocaMask;
4482 bool SwiftError = AlignRecord & SwiftErrorMask;
4483 Type *Ty = getTypeByID(Record[0]);
4484 if ((AlignRecord & ExplicitTypeMask) == 0) {
4485 auto *PTy = dyn_cast_or_null<PointerType>(Ty);
4486 if (!PTy)
4487 return error("Old-style alloca with a non-pointer type");
4488 Ty = PTy->getElementType();
4489 }
4490 Type *OpTy = getTypeByID(Record[1]);
4491 Value *Size = getFnValueByID(Record[2], OpTy);
4492 unsigned Align;
4493 if (Error Err = parseAlignmentValue(AlignRecord & ~FlagMask, Align)) {
4494 return Err;
4495 }
4496 if (!Ty || !Size)
4497 return error("Invalid record");
4498
4499 // FIXME: Make this an optional field.
4500 const DataLayout &DL = TheModule->getDataLayout();
4501 unsigned AS = DL.getAllocaAddrSpace();
4502
4503 AllocaInst *AI = new AllocaInst(Ty, AS, Size, Align);
4504 AI->setUsedWithInAlloca(InAlloca);
4505 AI->setSwiftError(SwiftError);
4506 I = AI;
4507 InstructionList.push_back(I);
4508 break;
4509 }
4510 case bitc::FUNC_CODE_INST_LOAD: { // LOAD: [opty, op, align, vol]
4511 unsigned OpNum = 0;
4512 Value *Op;
4513 if (getValueTypePair(Record, OpNum, NextValueNo, Op) ||
4514 (OpNum + 2 != Record.size() && OpNum + 3 != Record.size()))
4515 return error("Invalid record");
4516
4517 Type *Ty = nullptr;
4518 if (OpNum + 3 == Record.size())
4519 Ty = getTypeByID(Record[OpNum++]);
4520 if (Error Err = typeCheckLoadStoreInst(Ty, Op->getType()))
4521 return Err;
4522 if (!Ty)
4523 Ty = cast<PointerType>(Op->getType())->getElementType();
4524
4525 unsigned Align;
4526 if (Error Err = parseAlignmentValue(Record[OpNum], Align))
4527 return Err;
4528 I = new LoadInst(Ty, Op, "", Record[OpNum + 1], Align);
4529
4530 InstructionList.push_back(I);
4531 break;
4532 }
4533 case bitc::FUNC_CODE_INST_LOADATOMIC: {
4534 // LOADATOMIC: [opty, op, align, vol, ordering, ssid]
4535 unsigned OpNum = 0;
4536 Value *Op;
4537 if (getValueTypePair(Record, OpNum, NextValueNo, Op) ||
4538 (OpNum + 4 != Record.size() && OpNum + 5 != Record.size()))
4539 return error("Invalid record");
4540
4541 Type *Ty = nullptr;
4542 if (OpNum + 5 == Record.size())
4543 Ty = getTypeByID(Record[OpNum++]);
4544 if (Error Err = typeCheckLoadStoreInst(Ty, Op->getType()))
4545 return Err;
4546 if (!Ty)
4547 Ty = cast<PointerType>(Op->getType())->getElementType();
4548
4549 AtomicOrdering Ordering = getDecodedOrdering(Record[OpNum + 2]);
4550 if (Ordering == AtomicOrdering::NotAtomic ||
4551 Ordering == AtomicOrdering::Release ||
4552 Ordering == AtomicOrdering::AcquireRelease)
4553 return error("Invalid record");
4554 if (Ordering != AtomicOrdering::NotAtomic && Record[OpNum] == 0)
4555 return error("Invalid record");
4556 SyncScope::ID SSID = getDecodedSyncScopeID(Record[OpNum + 3]);
4557
4558 unsigned Align;
4559 if (Error Err = parseAlignmentValue(Record[OpNum], Align))
4560 return Err;
4561 I = new LoadInst(Ty, Op, "", Record[OpNum + 1], Align, Ordering, SSID);
4562
4563 InstructionList.push_back(I);
4564 break;
4565 }
4566 case bitc::FUNC_CODE_INST_STORE:
4567 case bitc::FUNC_CODE_INST_STORE_OLD: { // STORE2:[ptrty, ptr, val, align, vol]
4568 unsigned OpNum = 0;
4569 Value *Val, *Ptr;
4570 if (getValueTypePair(Record, OpNum, NextValueNo, Ptr) ||
4571 (BitCode == bitc::FUNC_CODE_INST_STORE
4572 ? getValueTypePair(Record, OpNum, NextValueNo, Val)
4573 : popValue(Record, OpNum, NextValueNo,
4574 cast<PointerType>(Ptr->getType())->getElementType(),
4575 Val)) ||
4576 OpNum + 2 != Record.size())
4577 return error("Invalid record");
4578
4579 if (Error Err = typeCheckLoadStoreInst(Val->getType(), Ptr->getType()))
4580 return Err;
4581 unsigned Align;
4582 if (Error Err = parseAlignmentValue(Record[OpNum], Align))
4583 return Err;
4584 I = new StoreInst(Val, Ptr, Record[OpNum+1], Align);
4585 InstructionList.push_back(I);
4586 break;
4587 }
4588 case bitc::FUNC_CODE_INST_STOREATOMIC:
4589 case bitc::FUNC_CODE_INST_STOREATOMIC_OLD: {
4590 // STOREATOMIC: [ptrty, ptr, val, align, vol, ordering, ssid]
4591 unsigned OpNum = 0;
4592 Value *Val, *Ptr;
4593 if (getValueTypePair(Record, OpNum, NextValueNo, Ptr) ||
4594 !isa<PointerType>(Ptr->getType()) ||
4595 (BitCode == bitc::FUNC_CODE_INST_STOREATOMIC
4596 ? getValueTypePair(Record, OpNum, NextValueNo, Val)
4597 : popValue(Record, OpNum, NextValueNo,
4598 cast<PointerType>(Ptr->getType())->getElementType(),
4599 Val)) ||
4600 OpNum + 4 != Record.size())
4601 return error("Invalid record");
4602
4603 if (Error Err = typeCheckLoadStoreInst(Val->getType(), Ptr->getType()))
4604 return Err;
4605 AtomicOrdering Ordering = getDecodedOrdering(Record[OpNum + 2]);
4606 if (Ordering == AtomicOrdering::NotAtomic ||
4607 Ordering == AtomicOrdering::Acquire ||
4608 Ordering == AtomicOrdering::AcquireRelease)
4609 return error("Invalid record");
4610 SyncScope::ID SSID = getDecodedSyncScopeID(Record[OpNum + 3]);
4611 if (Ordering != AtomicOrdering::NotAtomic && Record[OpNum] == 0)
4612 return error("Invalid record");
4613
4614 unsigned Align;
4615 if (Error Err = parseAlignmentValue(Record[OpNum], Align))
4616 return Err;
4617 I = new StoreInst(Val, Ptr, Record[OpNum+1], Align, Ordering, SSID);
4618 InstructionList.push_back(I);
4619 break;
4620 }
4621 case bitc::FUNC_CODE_INST_CMPXCHG_OLD:
4622 case bitc::FUNC_CODE_INST_CMPXCHG: {
4623 // CMPXCHG:[ptrty, ptr, cmp, new, vol, successordering, ssid,
4624 // failureordering?, isweak?]
4625 unsigned OpNum = 0;
4626 Value *Ptr, *Cmp, *New;
4627 if (getValueTypePair(Record, OpNum, NextValueNo, Ptr) ||
4628 (BitCode == bitc::FUNC_CODE_INST_CMPXCHG
4629 ? getValueTypePair(Record, OpNum, NextValueNo, Cmp)
4630 : popValue(Record, OpNum, NextValueNo,
4631 cast<PointerType>(Ptr->getType())->getElementType(),
4632 Cmp)) ||
4633 popValue(Record, OpNum, NextValueNo, Cmp->getType(), New) ||
4634 Record.size() < OpNum + 3 || Record.size() > OpNum + 5)
4635 return error("Invalid record");
4636 AtomicOrdering SuccessOrdering = getDecodedOrdering(Record[OpNum + 1]);
4637 if (SuccessOrdering == AtomicOrdering::NotAtomic ||
4638 SuccessOrdering == AtomicOrdering::Unordered)
4639 return error("Invalid record");
4640 SyncScope::ID SSID = getDecodedSyncScopeID(Record[OpNum + 2]);
4641
4642 if (Error Err = typeCheckLoadStoreInst(Cmp->getType(), Ptr->getType()))
4643 return Err;
4644 AtomicOrdering FailureOrdering;
4645 if (Record.size() < 7)
4646 FailureOrdering =
4647 AtomicCmpXchgInst::getStrongestFailureOrdering(SuccessOrdering);
4648 else
4649 FailureOrdering = getDecodedOrdering(Record[OpNum + 3]);
4650
4651 I = new AtomicCmpXchgInst(Ptr, Cmp, New, SuccessOrdering, FailureOrdering,
4652 SSID);
4653 cast<AtomicCmpXchgInst>(I)->setVolatile(Record[OpNum]);
4654
4655 if (Record.size() < 8) {
4656 // Before weak cmpxchgs existed, the instruction simply returned the
4657 // value loaded from memory, so bitcode files from that era will be
4658 // expecting the first component of a modern cmpxchg.
4659 CurBB->getInstList().push_back(I);
4660 I = ExtractValueInst::Create(I, 0);
4661 } else {
4662 cast<AtomicCmpXchgInst>(I)->setWeak(Record[OpNum+4]);
4663 }
4664
4665 InstructionList.push_back(I);
4666 break;
4667 }
4668 case bitc::FUNC_CODE_INST_ATOMICRMW: {
4669 // ATOMICRMW:[ptrty, ptr, val, op, vol, ordering, ssid]
4670 unsigned OpNum = 0;
4671 Value *Ptr, *Val;
4672 if (getValueTypePair(Record, OpNum, NextValueNo, Ptr) ||
4673 !isa<PointerType>(Ptr->getType()) ||
4674 popValue(Record, OpNum, NextValueNo,
4675 cast<PointerType>(Ptr->getType())->getElementType(), Val) ||
4676 OpNum+4 != Record.size())
4677 return error("Invalid record");
4678 AtomicRMWInst::BinOp Operation = getDecodedRMWOperation(Record[OpNum]);
4679 if (Operation < AtomicRMWInst::FIRST_BINOP ||
4680 Operation > AtomicRMWInst::LAST_BINOP)
4681 return error("Invalid record");
4682 AtomicOrdering Ordering = getDecodedOrdering(Record[OpNum + 2]);
4683 if (Ordering == AtomicOrdering::NotAtomic ||
4684 Ordering == AtomicOrdering::Unordered)
4685 return error("Invalid record");
4686 SyncScope::ID SSID = getDecodedSyncScopeID(Record[OpNum + 3]);
4687 I = new AtomicRMWInst(Operation, Ptr, Val, Ordering, SSID);
4688 cast<AtomicRMWInst>(I)->setVolatile(Record[OpNum+1]);
4689 InstructionList.push_back(I);
4690 break;
4691 }
4692 case bitc::FUNC_CODE_INST_FENCE: { // FENCE:[ordering, ssid]
4693 if (2 != Record.size())
4694 return error("Invalid record");
4695 AtomicOrdering Ordering = getDecodedOrdering(Record[0]);
4696 if (Ordering == AtomicOrdering::NotAtomic ||
4697 Ordering == AtomicOrdering::Unordered ||
4698 Ordering == AtomicOrdering::Monotonic)
4699 return error("Invalid record");
4700 SyncScope::ID SSID = getDecodedSyncScopeID(Record[1]);
4701 I = new FenceInst(Context, Ordering, SSID);
4702 InstructionList.push_back(I);
4703 break;
4704 }
4705 case bitc::FUNC_CODE_INST_CALL: {
4706 // CALL: [paramattrs, cc, fmf, fnty, fnid, arg0, arg1...]
4707 if (Record.size() < 3)
4708 return error("Invalid record");
4709
4710 unsigned OpNum = 0;
4711 AttributeList PAL = getAttributes(Record[OpNum++]);
4712 unsigned CCInfo = Record[OpNum++];
4713
4714 FastMathFlags FMF;
4715 if ((CCInfo >> bitc::CALL_FMF) & 1) {
4716 FMF = getDecodedFastMathFlags(Record[OpNum++]);
4717 if (!FMF.any())
4718 return error("Fast math flags indicator set for call with no FMF");
4719 }
4720
4721 FunctionType *FTy = nullptr;
4722 if (CCInfo >> bitc::CALL_EXPLICIT_TYPE & 1 &&
4723 !(FTy = dyn_cast<FunctionType>(getTypeByID(Record[OpNum++]))))
4724 return error("Explicit call type is not a function type");
4725
4726 Value *Callee;
4727 if (getValueTypePair(Record, OpNum, NextValueNo, Callee))
4728 return error("Invalid record");
4729
4730 PointerType *OpTy = dyn_cast<PointerType>(Callee->getType());
4731 if (!OpTy)
4732 return error("Callee is not a pointer type");
4733 if (!FTy) {
4734 FTy = dyn_cast<FunctionType>(OpTy->getElementType());
4735 if (!FTy)
4736 return error("Callee is not of pointer to function type");
4737 } else if (OpTy->getElementType() != FTy)
4738 return error("Explicit call type does not match pointee type of "
4739 "callee operand");
4740 if (Record.size() < FTy->getNumParams() + OpNum)
4741 return error("Insufficient operands to call");
4742
4743 SmallVector<Value*, 16> Args;
4744 // Read the fixed params.
4745 for (unsigned i = 0, e = FTy->getNumParams(); i != e; ++i, ++OpNum) {
4746 if (FTy->getParamType(i)->isLabelTy())
4747 Args.push_back(getBasicBlock(Record[OpNum]));
4748 else
4749 Args.push_back(getValue(Record, OpNum, NextValueNo,
4750 FTy->getParamType(i)));
4751 if (!Args.back())
4752 return error("Invalid record");
4753 }
4754
4755 // Read type/value pairs for varargs params.
4756 if (!FTy->isVarArg()) {
4757 if (OpNum != Record.size())
4758 return error("Invalid record");
4759 } else {
4760 while (OpNum != Record.size()) {
4761 Value *Op;
4762 if (getValueTypePair(Record, OpNum, NextValueNo, Op))
4763 return error("Invalid record");
4764 Args.push_back(Op);
4765 }
4766 }
4767
4768 I = CallInst::Create(FTy, Callee, Args, OperandBundles);
4769 OperandBundles.clear();
4770 InstructionList.push_back(I);
4771 cast<CallInst>(I)->setCallingConv(
4772 static_cast<CallingConv::ID>((0x7ff & CCInfo) >> bitc::CALL_CCONV));
4773 CallInst::TailCallKind TCK = CallInst::TCK_None;
4774 if (CCInfo & 1 << bitc::CALL_TAIL)
4775 TCK = CallInst::TCK_Tail;
4776 if (CCInfo & (1 << bitc::CALL_MUSTTAIL))
4777 TCK = CallInst::TCK_MustTail;
4778 if (CCInfo & (1 << bitc::CALL_NOTAIL))
4779 TCK = CallInst::TCK_NoTail;
4780 cast<CallInst>(I)->setTailCallKind(TCK);
4781 cast<CallInst>(I)->setAttributes(PAL);
4782 propagateByValTypes(cast<CallBase>(I));
4783 if (FMF.any()) {
4784 if (!isa<FPMathOperator>(I))
4785 return error("Fast-math-flags specified for call without "
4786 "floating-point scalar or vector return type");
4787 I->setFastMathFlags(FMF);
4788 }
4789 break;
4790 }
4791 case bitc::FUNC_CODE_INST_VAARG: { // VAARG: [valistty, valist, instty]
4792 if (Record.size() < 3)
4793 return error("Invalid record");
4794 Type *OpTy = getTypeByID(Record[0]);
4795 Value *Op = getValue(Record, 1, NextValueNo, OpTy);
4796 Type *ResTy = getTypeByID(Record[2]);
4797 if (!OpTy || !Op || !ResTy)
4798 return error("Invalid record");
4799 I = new VAArgInst(Op, ResTy);
4800 InstructionList.push_back(I);
4801 break;
4802 }
4803
4804 case bitc::FUNC_CODE_OPERAND_BUNDLE: {
4805 // A call or an invoke can be optionally prefixed with some variable
4806 // number of operand bundle blocks. These blocks are read into
4807 // OperandBundles and consumed at the next call or invoke instruction.
4808
4809 if (Record.size() < 1 || Record[0] >= BundleTags.size())
4810 return error("Invalid record");
4811
4812 std::vector<Value *> Inputs;
4813
4814 unsigned OpNum = 1;
4815 while (OpNum != Record.size()) {
4816 Value *Op;
4817 if (getValueTypePair(Record, OpNum, NextValueNo, Op))
4818 return error("Invalid record");
4819 Inputs.push_back(Op);
4820 }
4821
4822 OperandBundles.emplace_back(BundleTags[Record[0]], std::move(Inputs));
4823 continue;
4824 }
4825 }
4826
4827 // Add instruction to end of current BB. If there is no current BB, reject
4828 // this file.
4829 if (!CurBB) {
4830 I->deleteValue();
4831 return error("Invalid instruction with no BB");
4832 }
4833 if (!OperandBundles.empty()) {
4834 I->deleteValue();
4835 return error("Operand bundles found with no consumer");
4836 }
4837 CurBB->getInstList().push_back(I);
4838
4839 // If this was a terminator instruction, move to the next block.
4840 if (I->isTerminator()) {
4841 ++CurBBNo;
4842 CurBB = CurBBNo < FunctionBBs.size() ? FunctionBBs[CurBBNo] : nullptr;
4843 }
4844
4845 // Non-void values get registered in the value table for future use.
4846 if (I && !I->getType()->isVoidTy())
4847 ValueList.assignValue(I, NextValueNo++);
4848 }
4849
4850OutOfRecordLoop:
4851
4852 if (!OperandBundles.empty())
4853 return error("Operand bundles found with no consumer");
4854
4855 // Check the function list for unresolved values.
4856 if (Argument *A = dyn_cast<Argument>(ValueList.back())) {
4857 if (!A->getParent()) {
4858 // We found at least one unresolved value. Nuke them all to avoid leaks.
4859 for (unsigned i = ModuleValueListSize, e = ValueList.size(); i != e; ++i){
4860 if ((A = dyn_cast_or_null<Argument>(ValueList[i])) && !A->getParent()) {
4861 A->replaceAllUsesWith(UndefValue::get(A->getType()));
4862 delete A;
4863 }
4864 }
4865 return error("Never resolved value found in function");
4866 }
4867 }
4868
4869 // Unexpected unresolved metadata about to be dropped.
4870 if (MDLoader->hasFwdRefs())
4871 return error("Invalid function metadata: outgoing forward refs");
4872
4873 // Trim the value list down to the size it was before we parsed this function.
4874 ValueList.shrinkTo(ModuleValueListSize);
4875 MDLoader->shrinkTo(ModuleMDLoaderSize);
4876 std::vector<BasicBlock*>().swap(FunctionBBs);
4877 return Error::success();
4878}
4879
4880/// Find the function body in the bitcode stream
4881Error BitcodeReader::findFunctionInStream(
4882 Function *F,
4883 DenseMap<Function *, uint64_t>::iterator DeferredFunctionInfoIterator) {
4884 while (DeferredFunctionInfoIterator->second == 0) {
4885 // This is the fallback handling for the old format bitcode that
4886 // didn't contain the function index in the VST, or when we have
4887 // an anonymous function which would not have a VST entry.
4888 // Assert that we have one of those two cases.
4889 assert(VSTOffset == 0 || !F->hasName());
4890 // Parse the next body in the stream and set its position in the
4891 // DeferredFunctionInfo map.
4892 if (Error Err = rememberAndSkipFunctionBodies())
4893 return Err;
4894 }
4895 return Error::success();
4896}
4897
4898SyncScope::ID BitcodeReader::getDecodedSyncScopeID(unsigned Val) {
4899 if (Val == SyncScope::SingleThread || Val == SyncScope::System)
4900 return SyncScope::ID(Val);
4901 if (Val >= SSIDs.size())
4902 return SyncScope::System; // Map unknown synchronization scopes to system.
4903 return SSIDs[Val];
4904}
