4906//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
4907// GVMaterializer implementation
4908//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
4909
4910Error BitcodeReader::materialize(GlobalValue *GV) {
4911 Function *F = dyn_cast<Function>(GV);
4912 // If it's not a function or is already material, ignore the request.
4913 if (!F || !F->isMaterializable())
4914 return Error::success();
4915
4916 DenseMap<Function*, uint64_t>::iterator DFII = DeferredFunctionInfo.find(F);
4917 assert(DFII != DeferredFunctionInfo.end() && "Deferred function not found!");
4918 // If its position is recorded as 0, its body is somewhere in the stream
4919 // but we haven't seen it yet.
4920 if (DFII->second == 0)
4921 if (Error Err = findFunctionInStream(F, DFII))
4922 return Err;
4923
4924 // Materialize metadata before parsing any function bodies.
4925 if (Error Err = materializeMetadata())
4926 return Err;
4927
4928 // Move the bit stream to the saved position of the deferred function body.
4929 Stream.JumpToBit(DFII->second);
4930
4931 if (Error Err = parseFunctionBody(F))
4932 return Err;
4933 F->setIsMaterializable(false);
4934
4935 if (StripDebugInfo)
4936 stripDebugInfo(*F);
4937
4938 // Upgrade any old intrinsic calls in the function.
4939 for (auto &I : UpgradedIntrinsics) {
4940 for (auto UI = I.first->materialized_user_begin(), UE = I.first->user_end();
4941 UI != UE;) {
4942 User *U = *UI;
4943 ++UI;
4944 if (CallInst *CI = dyn_cast<CallInst>(U))
4945 UpgradeIntrinsicCall(CI, I.second);
4946 }
4947 }
4948
4949 // Update calls to the remangled intrinsics
4950 for (auto &I : RemangledIntrinsics)
4951 for (auto UI = I.first->materialized_user_begin(), UE = I.first->user_end();
4952 UI != UE;)
4953 // Don't expect any other users than call sites
4954 CallSite(*UI++).setCalledFunction(I.second);
4955
4956 // Finish fn->subprogram upgrade for materialized functions.
4957 if (DISubprogram *SP = MDLoader->lookupSubprogramForFunction(F))
4958 F->setSubprogram(SP);
4959
4960 // Check if the TBAA Metadata are valid, otherwise we will need to strip them.
4961 if (!MDLoader->isStrippingTBAA()) {
4962 for (auto &I : instructions(F)) {
4963 MDNode *TBAA = I.getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_tbaa);
4964 if (!TBAA || TBAAVerifyHelper.visitTBAAMetadata(I, TBAA))
4965 continue;
4966 MDLoader->setStripTBAA(true);
4967 stripTBAA(F->getParent());
4968 }
4969 }
4970
4971 // Bring in any functions that this function forward-referenced via
4972 // blockaddresses.
4973 return materializeForwardReferencedFunctions();
4974}
4975
4976Error BitcodeReader::materializeModule() {
4977 if (Error Err = materializeMetadata())
4978 return Err;
4979
4980 // Promise to materialize all forward references.
4981 WillMaterializeAllForwardRefs = true;
4982
4983 // Iterate over the module, deserializing any functions that are still on
4984 // disk.
4985 for (Function &F : *TheModule) {
4986 if (Error Err = materialize(&F))
4987 return Err;
4988 }
4989 // At this point, if there are any function bodies, parse the rest of
4990 // the bits in the module past the last function block we have recorded
4991 // through either lazy scanning or the VST.
4992 if (LastFunctionBlockBit || NextUnreadBit)
4993 if (Error Err = parseModule(LastFunctionBlockBit > NextUnreadBit
4994 ? LastFunctionBlockBit
4995 : NextUnreadBit))
4996 return Err;
4997
4998 // Check that all block address forward references got resolved (as we
4999 // promised above).
5000 if (!BasicBlockFwdRefs.empty())
5001 return error("Never resolved function from blockaddress");
5002
5003 // Upgrade any intrinsic calls that slipped through (should not happen!) and
5004 // delete the old functions to clean up. We can't do this unless the entire
5005 // module is materialized because there could always be another function body
5006 // with calls to the old function.
5007 for (auto &I : UpgradedIntrinsics) {
5008 for (auto *U : I.first->users()) {
5009 if (CallInst *CI = dyn_cast<CallInst>(U))
5010 UpgradeIntrinsicCall(CI, I.second);
5011 }
5012 if (!I.first->use_empty())
5013 I.first->replaceAllUsesWith(I.second);
5014 I.first->eraseFromParent();
5015 }
5016 UpgradedIntrinsics.clear();
5017 // Do the same for remangled intrinsics
5018 for (auto &I : RemangledIntrinsics) {
5019 I.first->replaceAllUsesWith(I.second);
5020 I.first->eraseFromParent();
5021 }
5022 RemangledIntrinsics.clear();
5023
5024 UpgradeDebugInfo(*TheModule);
5025
5026 UpgradeModuleFlags(*TheModule);
5027
5028 UpgradeRetainReleaseMarker(*TheModule);
5029
5030 return Error::success();
5031}

5058
5059void ModuleSummaryIndexBitcodeReader::setValueGUID(
5060 uint64_t ValueID, StringRef ValueName, GlobalValue::LinkageTypes Linkage,
5061 StringRef SourceFileName) {
5062 std::string GlobalId =
5063 GlobalValue::getGlobalIdentifier(ValueName, Linkage, SourceFileName);
5064 auto ValueGUID = GlobalValue::getGUID(GlobalId);
5065 auto OriginalNameID = ValueGUID;
5066 if (GlobalValue::isLocalLinkage(Linkage))
5067 OriginalNameID = GlobalValue::getGUID(ValueName);
5068 if (PrintSummaryGUIDs)
5069 dbgs() << "GUID " << ValueGUID << "(" << OriginalNameID << ") is "
5070 << ValueName << "\n";
5071
5072 // UseStrtab is false for legacy summary formats and value names are
5073 // created on stack. In that case we save the name in a string saver in
5074 // the index so that the value name can be recorded.
5075 ValueIdToValueInfoMap[ValueID] = std::make_pair(
5076 TheIndex.getOrInsertValueInfo(
5077 ValueGUID,
5078 UseStrtab ? ValueName : TheIndex.saveString(ValueName)),
5079 OriginalNameID);
5080}
5081
5082// Specialized value symbol table parser used when reading module index
5083// blocks where we don't actually create global values. The parsed information
5084// is saved in the bitcode reader for use when later parsing summaries.
5085Error ModuleSummaryIndexBitcodeReader::parseValueSymbolTable(
5086 uint64_t Offset,
5087 DenseMap<unsigned, GlobalValue::LinkageTypes> &ValueIdToLinkageMap) {
5088 // With a strtab the VST is not required to parse the summary.
5089 if (UseStrtab)
5090 return Error::success();
5091
5092 assert(Offset > 0 && "Expected non-zero VST offset");
5093 uint64_t CurrentBit = jumpToValueSymbolTable(Offset, Stream);
5094
5095 if (Stream.EnterSubBlock(bitc::VALUE_SYMTAB_BLOCK_ID))
5096 return error("Invalid record");
5097
5098 SmallVector<uint64_t, 64> Record;
5099
5100 // Read all the records for this value table.
5101 SmallString<128> ValueName;
5102
5103 while (true) {
5104 BitstreamEntry Entry = Stream.advanceSkippingSubblocks();
5105
5106 switch (Entry.Kind) {
5107 case BitstreamEntry::SubBlock: // Handled for us already.
5108 case BitstreamEntry::Error:
5109 return error("Malformed block");
5110 case BitstreamEntry::EndBlock:
5111 // Done parsing VST, jump back to wherever we came from.
5112 Stream.JumpToBit(CurrentBit);
5113 return Error::success();
5114 case BitstreamEntry::Record:
5115 // The interesting case.
5116 break;
5117 }
5118
5119 // Read a record.
5120 Record.clear();
5121 switch (Stream.readRecord(Entry.ID, Record)) {
5122 default: // Default behavior: ignore (e.g. VST_CODE_BBENTRY records).
5123 break;
5124 case bitc::VST_CODE_ENTRY: { // VST_CODE_ENTRY: [valueid, namechar x N]
5125 if (convertToString(Record, 1, ValueName))
5126 return error("Invalid record");
5127 unsigned ValueID = Record[0];
5128 assert(!SourceFileName.empty());
5129 auto VLI = ValueIdToLinkageMap.find(ValueID);
5130 assert(VLI != ValueIdToLinkageMap.end() &&
5131 "No linkage found for VST entry?");
5132 auto Linkage = VLI->second;
5133 setValueGUID(ValueID, ValueName, Linkage, SourceFileName);
5134 ValueName.clear();
5135 break;
5136 }
5137 case bitc::VST_CODE_FNENTRY: {
5138 // VST_CODE_FNENTRY: [valueid, offset, namechar x N]
5139 if (convertToString(Record, 2, ValueName))
5140 return error("Invalid record");
5141 unsigned ValueID = Record[0];
5142 assert(!SourceFileName.empty());
5143 auto VLI = ValueIdToLinkageMap.find(ValueID);
5144 assert(VLI != ValueIdToLinkageMap.end() &&
5145 "No linkage found for VST entry?");
5146 auto Linkage = VLI->second;
5147 setValueGUID(ValueID, ValueName, Linkage, SourceFileName);
5148 ValueName.clear();
5149 break;
5150 }
5151 case bitc::VST_CODE_COMBINED_ENTRY: {
5152 // VST_CODE_COMBINED_ENTRY: [valueid, refguid]
5153 unsigned ValueID = Record[0];
5154 GlobalValue::GUID RefGUID = Record[1];
5155 // The "original name", which is the second value of the pair will be
5156 // overriden later by a FS_COMBINED_ORIGINAL_NAME in the combined index.
5157 ValueIdToValueInfoMap[ValueID] =
5158 std::make_pair(TheIndex.getOrInsertValueInfo(RefGUID), RefGUID);
5159 break;
5160 }
5161 }
5162 }
5163}
5164
5165// Parse just the blocks needed for building the index out of the module.
5166// At the end of this routine the module Index is populated with a map
5167// from global value id to GlobalValueSummary objects.
5168Error ModuleSummaryIndexBitcodeReader::parseModule() {
5169 if (Stream.EnterSubBlock(bitc::MODULE_BLOCK_ID))
5170 return error("Invalid record");
5171
5172 SmallVector<uint64_t, 64> Record;
5173 DenseMap<unsigned, GlobalValue::LinkageTypes> ValueIdToLinkageMap;
5174 unsigned ValueId = 0;
5175
5176 // Read the index for this module.
5177 while (true) {
5178 BitstreamEntry Entry = Stream.advance();
5179
5180 switch (Entry.Kind) {
5181 case BitstreamEntry::Error:
5182 return error("Malformed block");
5183 case BitstreamEntry::EndBlock:
5184 return Error::success();
5185
5186 case BitstreamEntry::SubBlock:
5187 switch (Entry.ID) {
5188 default: // Skip unknown content.
5189 if (Stream.SkipBlock())
5190 return error("Invalid record");
5191 break;
5192 case bitc::BLOCKINFO_BLOCK_ID:
5193 // Need to parse these to get abbrev ids (e.g. for VST)
5194 if (readBlockInfo())
5195 return error("Malformed block");
5196 break;
5197 case bitc::VALUE_SYMTAB_BLOCK_ID:
5198 // Should have been parsed earlier via VSTOffset, unless there
5199 // is no summary section.
5200 assert(((SeenValueSymbolTable && VSTOffset > 0) ||
5201 !SeenGlobalValSummary) &&
5202 "Expected early VST parse via VSTOffset record");
5203 if (Stream.SkipBlock())
5204 return error("Invalid record");
5205 break;
5206 case bitc::GLOBALVAL_SUMMARY_BLOCK_ID:
5207 case bitc::FULL_LTO_GLOBALVAL_SUMMARY_BLOCK_ID:
5208 // Add the module if it is a per-module index (has a source file name).
5209 if (!SourceFileName.empty())
5210 addThisModule();
5211 assert(!SeenValueSymbolTable &&
5212 "Already read VST when parsing summary block?");
5213 // We might not have a VST if there were no values in the
5214 // summary. An empty summary block generated when we are
5215 // performing ThinLTO compiles so we don't later invoke
5216 // the regular LTO process on them.
5217 if (VSTOffset > 0) {
5218 if (Error Err = parseValueSymbolTable(VSTOffset, ValueIdToLinkageMap))
5219 return Err;
5220 SeenValueSymbolTable = true;
5221 }
5222 SeenGlobalValSummary = true;
5223 if (Error Err = parseEntireSummary(Entry.ID))
5224 return Err;
5225 break;
5226 case bitc::MODULE_STRTAB_BLOCK_ID:
5227 if (Error Err = parseModuleStringTable())
5228 return Err;
5229 break;
5230 }
5231 continue;
5232
5233 case BitstreamEntry::Record: {
5234 Record.clear();
5235 auto BitCode = Stream.readRecord(Entry.ID, Record);
5236 switch (BitCode) {
5237 default:
5238 break; // Default behavior, ignore unknown content.
5239 case bitc::MODULE_CODE_VERSION: {
5240 if (Error Err = parseVersionRecord(Record).takeError())
5241 return Err;
5242 break;
5243 }
5244 /// MODULE_CODE_SOURCE_FILENAME: [namechar x N]
5245 case bitc::MODULE_CODE_SOURCE_FILENAME: {
5246 SmallString<128> ValueName;
5247 if (convertToString(Record, 0, ValueName))
5248 return error("Invalid record");
5249 SourceFileName = ValueName.c_str();
5250 break;
5251 }
5252 /// MODULE_CODE_HASH: [5*i32]
5253 case bitc::MODULE_CODE_HASH: {
5254 if (Record.size() != 5)
5255 return error("Invalid hash length " + Twine(Record.size()).str());
5256 auto &Hash = getThisModule()->second.second;
5257 int Pos = 0;
5258 for (auto &Val : Record) {
5259 assert(!(Val >> 32) && "Unexpected high bits set");
5260 Hash[Pos++] = Val;
5261 }
5262 break;
5263 }
5264 /// MODULE_CODE_VSTOFFSET: [offset]
5265 case bitc::MODULE_CODE_VSTOFFSET:
5266 if (Record.size() < 1)
5267 return error("Invalid record");
5268 // Note that we subtract 1 here because the offset is relative to one
5269 // word before the start of the identification or module block, which
5270 // was historically always the start of the regular bitcode header.
5271 VSTOffset = Record[0] - 1;
5272 break;
5273 // v1 GLOBALVAR: [pointer type, isconst, initid, linkage, ...]
5274 // v1 FUNCTION: [type, callingconv, isproto, linkage, ...]
5275 // v1 ALIAS: [alias type, addrspace, aliasee val#, linkage, ...]
5276 // v2: [strtab offset, strtab size, v1]
5277 case bitc::MODULE_CODE_GLOBALVAR:
5278 case bitc::MODULE_CODE_FUNCTION:
5279 case bitc::MODULE_CODE_ALIAS: {
5280 StringRef Name;
5281 ArrayRef<uint64_t> GVRecord;
5282 std::tie(Name, GVRecord) = readNameFromStrtab(Record);
5283 if (GVRecord.size() <= 3)
5284 return error("Invalid record");
5285 uint64_t RawLinkage = GVRecord[3];
5286 GlobalValue::LinkageTypes Linkage = getDecodedLinkage(RawLinkage);
5287 if (!UseStrtab) {
5288 ValueIdToLinkageMap[ValueId++] = Linkage;
5289 break;
5290 }
5291
5292 setValueGUID(ValueId++, Name, Linkage, SourceFileName);
5293 break;
5294 }
5295 }
5296 }
5297 continue;
5298 }
5299 }
5300}
5301
5302std::vector<ValueInfo>
5303ModuleSummaryIndexBitcodeReader::makeRefList(ArrayRef<uint64_t> Record) {
5304 std::vector<ValueInfo> Ret;
5305 Ret.reserve(Record.size());
5306 for (uint64_t RefValueId : Record)
5307 Ret.push_back(getValueInfoFromValueId(RefValueId).first);
5308 return Ret;
5309}
5310
5311std::vector<FunctionSummary::EdgeTy>
5312ModuleSummaryIndexBitcodeReader::makeCallList(ArrayRef<uint64_t> Record,
5313 bool IsOldProfileFormat,
5314 bool HasProfile, bool HasRelBF) {
5315 std::vector<FunctionSummary::EdgeTy> Ret;
5316 Ret.reserve(Record.size());
5317 for (unsigned I = 0, E = Record.size(); I != E; ++I) {
5318 CalleeInfo::HotnessType Hotness = CalleeInfo::HotnessType::Unknown;
5319 uint64_t RelBF = 0;
5320 ValueInfo Callee = getValueInfoFromValueId(Record[I]).first;
5321 if (IsOldProfileFormat) {
5322 I += 1; // Skip old callsitecount field
5323 if (HasProfile)
5324 I += 1; // Skip old profilecount field
5325 } else if (HasProfile)
5326 Hotness = static_cast<CalleeInfo::HotnessType>(Record[++I]);
5327 else if (HasRelBF)
5328 RelBF = Record[++I];
5329 Ret.push_back(FunctionSummary::EdgeTy{Callee, CalleeInfo(Hotness, RelBF)});
5330 }
5331 return Ret;
5332}

5334static void
5335parseWholeProgramDevirtResolutionByArg(ArrayRef<uint64_t> Record, size_t &Slot,
5336 WholeProgramDevirtResolution &Wpd) {
5337 uint64_t ArgNum = Record[Slot++];
5338 WholeProgramDevirtResolution::ByArg &B =
5339 Wpd.ResByArg[{Record.begin() + Slot, Record.begin() + Slot + ArgNum}];
5340 Slot += ArgNum;
5341
5342 B.TheKind =
5343 static_cast<WholeProgramDevirtResolution::ByArg::Kind>(Record[Slot++]);
5344 B.Info = Record[Slot++];
5345 B.Byte = Record[Slot++];
5346 B.Bit = Record[Slot++];
5347}
5348
5349static void parseWholeProgramDevirtResolution(ArrayRef<uint64_t> Record,
5350 StringRef Strtab, size_t &Slot,
5351 TypeIdSummary &TypeId) {
5352 uint64_t Id = Record[Slot++];
5353 WholeProgramDevirtResolution &Wpd = TypeId.WPDRes[Id];
5354
5355 Wpd.TheKind = static_cast<WholeProgramDevirtResolution::Kind>(Record[Slot++]);
5356 Wpd.SingleImplName = {Strtab.data() + Record[Slot],
5357 static_cast<size_t>(Record[Slot + 1])};
5358 Slot += 2;
5359
5360 uint64_t ResByArgNum = Record[Slot++];
5361 for (uint64_t I = 0; I != ResByArgNum; ++I)
5362 parseWholeProgramDevirtResolutionByArg(Record, Slot, Wpd);
5363}
5364
5365static void parseTypeIdSummaryRecord(ArrayRef<uint64_t> Record,
5366 StringRef Strtab,
5367 ModuleSummaryIndex &TheIndex) {
5368 size_t Slot = 0;
5369 TypeIdSummary &TypeId = TheIndex.getOrInsertTypeIdSummary(
5370 {Strtab.data() + Record[Slot], static_cast<size_t>(Record[Slot + 1])});
5371 Slot += 2;
5372
5373 TypeId.TTRes.TheKind = static_cast<TypeTestResolution::Kind>(Record[Slot++]);
5374 TypeId.TTRes.SizeM1BitWidth = Record[Slot++];
5375 TypeId.TTRes.AlignLog2 = Record[Slot++];
5376 TypeId.TTRes.SizeM1 = Record[Slot++];
5377 TypeId.TTRes.BitMask = Record[Slot++];
5378 TypeId.TTRes.InlineBits = Record[Slot++];
5379
5380 while (Slot < Record.size())
5381 parseWholeProgramDevirtResolution(Record, Strtab, Slot, TypeId);
5382}
5383
5384static void setImmutableRefs(std::vector<ValueInfo> &Refs, unsigned Count) {
5385 // Read-only refs are in the end of the refs list.
5386 for (unsigned RefNo = Refs.size() - Count; RefNo < Refs.size(); ++RefNo)
5387 Refs[RefNo].setReadOnly();
5388}
5389
5390// Eagerly parse the entire summary block. This populates the GlobalValueSummary
5391// objects in the index.
5392Error ModuleSummaryIndexBitcodeReader::parseEntireSummary(unsigned ID) {
5393 if (Stream.EnterSubBlock(ID))
5394 return error("Invalid record");
5395 SmallVector<uint64_t, 64> Record;
5396
5397 // Parse version
5398 {
5399 BitstreamEntry Entry = Stream.advanceSkippingSubblocks();
5400 if (Entry.Kind != BitstreamEntry::Record)
5401 return error("Invalid Summary Block: record for version expected");
5402 if (Stream.readRecord(Entry.ID, Record) != bitc::FS_VERSION)
5403 return error("Invalid Summary Block: version expected");
5404 }
5405 const uint64_t Version = Record[0];
5406 const bool IsOldProfileFormat = Version == 1;
5407 if (Version < 1 || Version > 6)
5408 return error("Invalid summary version " + Twine(Version) +
5409 ". Version should be in the range [1-6].");
5410 Record.clear();
5411
5412 // Keep around the last seen summary to be used when we see an optional
5413 // "OriginalName" attachement.
5414 GlobalValueSummary *LastSeenSummary = nullptr;
5415 GlobalValue::GUID LastSeenGUID = 0;
5416
5417 // We can expect to see any number of type ID information records before
5418 // each function summary records; these variables store the information
5419 // collected so far so that it can be used to create the summary object.
5420 std::vector<GlobalValue::GUID> PendingTypeTests;
5421 std::vector<FunctionSummary::VFuncId> PendingTypeTestAssumeVCalls,
5422 PendingTypeCheckedLoadVCalls;
5423 std::vector<FunctionSummary::ConstVCall> PendingTypeTestAssumeConstVCalls,
5424 PendingTypeCheckedLoadConstVCalls;
5425
5426 while (true) {
5427 BitstreamEntry Entry = Stream.advanceSkippingSubblocks();
5428
5429 switch (Entry.Kind) {
5430 case BitstreamEntry::SubBlock: // Handled for us already.
5431 case BitstreamEntry::Error:
5432 return error("Malformed block");
5433 case BitstreamEntry::EndBlock:
5434 return Error::success();
5435 case BitstreamEntry::Record:
5436 // The interesting case.
5437 break;
5438 }
5439
5440 // Read a record. The record format depends on whether this
5441 // is a per-module index or a combined index file. In the per-module
5442 // case the records contain the associated value's ID for correlation
5443 // with VST entries. In the combined index the correlation is done
5444 // via the bitcode offset of the summary records (which were saved
5445 // in the combined index VST entries). The records also contain
5446 // information used for ThinLTO renaming and importing.
5447 Record.clear();
5448 auto BitCode = Stream.readRecord(Entry.ID, Record);
5449 switch (BitCode) {
5450 default: // Default behavior: ignore.
5451 break;
5452 case bitc::FS_FLAGS: { // [flags]
5453 uint64_t Flags = Record[0];
5454 // Scan flags.
5455 assert(Flags <= 0x1f && "Unexpected bits in flag");
5456
5457 // 1 bit: WithGlobalValueDeadStripping flag.
5458 // Set on combined index only.
5459 if (Flags & 0x1)
5460 TheIndex.setWithGlobalValueDeadStripping();
5461 // 1 bit: SkipModuleByDistributedBackend flag.
5462 // Set on combined index only.
5463 if (Flags & 0x2)
5464 TheIndex.setSkipModuleByDistributedBackend();
5465 // 1 bit: HasSyntheticEntryCounts flag.
5466 // Set on combined index only.
5467 if (Flags & 0x4)
5468 TheIndex.setHasSyntheticEntryCounts();
5469 // 1 bit: DisableSplitLTOUnit flag.
5470 // Set on per module indexes. It is up to the client to validate
5471 // the consistency of this flag across modules being linked.
5472 if (Flags & 0x8)
5473 TheIndex.setEnableSplitLTOUnit();
5474 // 1 bit: PartiallySplitLTOUnits flag.
5475 // Set on combined index only.
5476 if (Flags & 0x10)
5477 TheIndex.setPartiallySplitLTOUnits();
5478 break;
5479 }
5480 case bitc::FS_VALUE_GUID: { // [valueid, refguid]
5481 uint64_t ValueID = Record[0];
5482 GlobalValue::GUID RefGUID = Record[1];
5483 ValueIdToValueInfoMap[ValueID] =
5484 std::make_pair(TheIndex.getOrInsertValueInfo(RefGUID), RefGUID);
5485 break;
5486 }
5487 // FS_PERMODULE: [valueid, flags, instcount, fflags, numrefs,
5488 // numrefs x valueid, n x (valueid)]
5489 // FS_PERMODULE_PROFILE: [valueid, flags, instcount, fflags, numrefs,
5490 // numrefs x valueid,
5491 // n x (valueid, hotness)]
5492 // FS_PERMODULE_RELBF: [valueid, flags, instcount, fflags, numrefs,
5493 // numrefs x valueid,
5494 // n x (valueid, relblockfreq)]
5495 case bitc::FS_PERMODULE:
5496 case bitc::FS_PERMODULE_RELBF:
5497 case bitc::FS_PERMODULE_PROFILE: {
5498 unsigned ValueID = Record[0];
5499 uint64_t RawFlags = Record[1];
5500 unsigned InstCount = Record[2];
5501 uint64_t RawFunFlags = 0;
5502 unsigned NumRefs = Record[3];
5503 unsigned NumImmutableRefs = 0;
5504 int RefListStartIndex = 4;
5505 if (Version >= 4) {
5506 RawFunFlags = Record[3];
5507 NumRefs = Record[4];
5508 RefListStartIndex = 5;
5509 if (Version >= 5) {
5510 NumImmutableRefs = Record[5];
5511 RefListStartIndex = 6;
5512 }
5513 }
5514
5515 auto Flags = getDecodedGVSummaryFlags(RawFlags, Version);
5516 // The module path string ref set in the summary must be owned by the
5517 // index's module string table. Since we don't have a module path
5518 // string table section in the per-module index, we create a single
5519 // module path string table entry with an empty (0) ID to take
5520 // ownership.
5521 int CallGraphEdgeStartIndex = RefListStartIndex + NumRefs;
5522 assert(Record.size() >= RefListStartIndex + NumRefs &&
5523 "Record size inconsistent with number of references");
5524 std::vector<ValueInfo> Refs = makeRefList(
5525 ArrayRef<uint64_t>(Record).slice(RefListStartIndex, NumRefs));
5526 bool HasProfile = (BitCode == bitc::FS_PERMODULE_PROFILE);
5527 bool HasRelBF = (BitCode == bitc::FS_PERMODULE_RELBF);
5528 std::vector<FunctionSummary::EdgeTy> Calls = makeCallList(
5529 ArrayRef<uint64_t>(Record).slice(CallGraphEdgeStartIndex),
5530 IsOldProfileFormat, HasProfile, HasRelBF);
5531 setImmutableRefs(Refs, NumImmutableRefs);
5532 auto FS = llvm::make_unique<FunctionSummary>(
5533 Flags, InstCount, getDecodedFFlags(RawFunFlags), /*EntryCount=*/0,
5534 std::move(Refs), std::move(Calls), std::move(PendingTypeTests),
5535 std::move(PendingTypeTestAssumeVCalls),
5536 std::move(PendingTypeCheckedLoadVCalls),
5537 std::move(PendingTypeTestAssumeConstVCalls),
5538 std::move(PendingTypeCheckedLoadConstVCalls));
5539 PendingTypeTests.clear();
5540 PendingTypeTestAssumeVCalls.clear();
5541 PendingTypeCheckedLoadVCalls.clear();
5542 PendingTypeTestAssumeConstVCalls.clear();
5543 PendingTypeCheckedLoadConstVCalls.clear();
5544 auto VIAndOriginalGUID = getValueInfoFromValueId(ValueID);
5545 FS->setModulePath(getThisModule()->first());
5546 FS->setOriginalName(VIAndOriginalGUID.second);
5547 TheIndex.addGlobalValueSummary(VIAndOriginalGUID.first, std::move(FS));
5548 break;
5549 }
5550 // FS_ALIAS: [valueid, flags, valueid]
5551 // Aliases must be emitted (and parsed) after all FS_PERMODULE entries, as
5552 // they expect all aliasee summaries to be available.
5553 case bitc::FS_ALIAS: {
5554 unsigned ValueID = Record[0];
5555 uint64_t RawFlags = Record[1];
5556 unsigned AliaseeID = Record[2];
5557 auto Flags = getDecodedGVSummaryFlags(RawFlags, Version);
5558 auto AS = llvm::make_unique<AliasSummary>(Flags);
5559 // The module path string ref set in the summary must be owned by the
5560 // index's module string table. Since we don't have a module path
5561 // string table section in the per-module index, we create a single
5562 // module path string table entry with an empty (0) ID to take
5563 // ownership.
5564 AS->setModulePath(getThisModule()->first());
5565
5566 auto AliaseeVI = getValueInfoFromValueId(AliaseeID).first;
5567 auto AliaseeInModule = TheIndex.findSummaryInModule(AliaseeVI, ModulePath);
5568 if (!AliaseeInModule)
5569 return error("Alias expects aliasee summary to be parsed");
5570 AS->setAliasee(AliaseeVI, AliaseeInModule);
5571
5572 auto GUID = getValueInfoFromValueId(ValueID);
5573 AS->setOriginalName(GUID.second);
5574 TheIndex.addGlobalValueSummary(GUID.first, std::move(AS));
5575 break;
5576 }
5577 // FS_PERMODULE_GLOBALVAR_INIT_REFS: [valueid, flags, varflags, n x valueid]
5578 case bitc::FS_PERMODULE_GLOBALVAR_INIT_REFS: {
5579 unsigned ValueID = Record[0];
5580 uint64_t RawFlags = Record[1];
5581 unsigned RefArrayStart = 2;
5582 GlobalVarSummary::GVarFlags GVF;
5583 auto Flags = getDecodedGVSummaryFlags(RawFlags, Version);
5584 if (Version >= 5) {
5585 GVF = getDecodedGVarFlags(Record[2]);
5586 RefArrayStart = 3;
5587 }
5588 std::vector<ValueInfo> Refs =
5589 makeRefList(ArrayRef<uint64_t>(Record).slice(RefArrayStart));
5590 auto FS =
5591 llvm::make_unique<GlobalVarSummary>(Flags, GVF, std::move(Refs));
5592 FS->setModulePath(getThisModule()->first());
5593 auto GUID = getValueInfoFromValueId(ValueID);
5594 FS->setOriginalName(GUID.second);
5595 TheIndex.addGlobalValueSummary(GUID.first, std::move(FS));
5596 break;
5597 }
5598 // FS_COMBINED: [valueid, modid, flags, instcount, fflags, numrefs,
5599 // numrefs x valueid, n x (valueid)]
5600 // FS_COMBINED_PROFILE: [valueid, modid, flags, instcount, fflags, numrefs,
5601 // numrefs x valueid, n x (valueid, hotness)]
5602 case bitc::FS_COMBINED:
5603 case bitc::FS_COMBINED_PROFILE: {
5604 unsigned ValueID = Record[0];
5605 uint64_t ModuleId = Record[1];
5606 uint64_t RawFlags = Record[2];
5607 unsigned InstCount = Record[3];
5608 uint64_t RawFunFlags = 0;
5609 uint64_t EntryCount = 0;
5610 unsigned NumRefs = Record[4];
5611 unsigned NumImmutableRefs = 0;
5612 int RefListStartIndex = 5;
5613
5614 if (Version >= 4) {
5615 RawFunFlags = Record[4];
5616 RefListStartIndex = 6;
5617 size_t NumRefsIndex = 5;
5618 if (Version >= 5) {
5619 RefListStartIndex = 7;
5620 if (Version >= 6) {
5621 NumRefsIndex = 6;
5622 EntryCount = Record[5];
5623 RefListStartIndex = 8;
5624 }
5625 NumImmutableRefs = Record[RefListStartIndex - 1];
5626 }
5627 NumRefs = Record[NumRefsIndex];
5628 }
5629
5630 auto Flags = getDecodedGVSummaryFlags(RawFlags, Version);
5631 int CallGraphEdgeStartIndex = RefListStartIndex + NumRefs;
5632 assert(Record.size() >= RefListStartIndex + NumRefs &&
5633 "Record size inconsistent with number of references");
5634 std::vector<ValueInfo> Refs = makeRefList(
5635 ArrayRef<uint64_t>(Record).slice(RefListStartIndex, NumRefs));
5636 bool HasProfile = (BitCode == bitc::FS_COMBINED_PROFILE);
5637 std::vector<FunctionSummary::EdgeTy> Edges = makeCallList(
5638 ArrayRef<uint64_t>(Record).slice(CallGraphEdgeStartIndex),
5639 IsOldProfileFormat, HasProfile, false);
5640 ValueInfo VI = getValueInfoFromValueId(ValueID).first;
5641 setImmutableRefs(Refs, NumImmutableRefs);
5642 auto FS = llvm::make_unique<FunctionSummary>(
5643 Flags, InstCount, getDecodedFFlags(RawFunFlags), EntryCount,
5644 std::move(Refs), std::move(Edges), std::move(PendingTypeTests),
5645 std::move(PendingTypeTestAssumeVCalls),
5646 std::move(PendingTypeCheckedLoadVCalls),
5647 std::move(PendingTypeTestAssumeConstVCalls),
5648 std::move(PendingTypeCheckedLoadConstVCalls));
5649 PendingTypeTests.clear();
5650 PendingTypeTestAssumeVCalls.clear();
5651 PendingTypeCheckedLoadVCalls.clear();
5652 PendingTypeTestAssumeConstVCalls.clear();
5653 PendingTypeCheckedLoadConstVCalls.clear();
5654 LastSeenSummary = FS.get();
5655 LastSeenGUID = VI.getGUID();
5656 FS->setModulePath(ModuleIdMap[ModuleId]);
5657 TheIndex.addGlobalValueSummary(VI, std::move(FS));
5658 break;
5659 }
5660 // FS_COMBINED_ALIAS: [valueid, modid, flags, valueid]
5661 // Aliases must be emitted (and parsed) after all FS_COMBINED entries, as
5662 // they expect all aliasee summaries to be available.
5663 case bitc::FS_COMBINED_ALIAS: {
5664 unsigned ValueID = Record[0];
5665 uint64_t ModuleId = Record[1];
5666 uint64_t RawFlags = Record[2];
5667 unsigned AliaseeValueId = Record[3];
5668 auto Flags = getDecodedGVSummaryFlags(RawFlags, Version);
5669 auto AS = llvm::make_unique<AliasSummary>(Flags);
5670 LastSeenSummary = AS.get();
5671 AS->setModulePath(ModuleIdMap[ModuleId]);
5672
5673 auto AliaseeVI = getValueInfoFromValueId(AliaseeValueId).first;
5674 auto AliaseeInModule = TheIndex.findSummaryInModule(AliaseeVI, AS->modulePath());
5675 AS->setAliasee(AliaseeVI, AliaseeInModule);
5676
5677 ValueInfo VI = getValueInfoFromValueId(ValueID).first;
5678 LastSeenGUID = VI.getGUID();
5679 TheIndex.addGlobalValueSummary(VI, std::move(AS));
5680 break;
5681 }
5682 // FS_COMBINED_GLOBALVAR_INIT_REFS: [valueid, modid, flags, n x valueid]
5683 case bitc::FS_COMBINED_GLOBALVAR_INIT_REFS: {
5684 unsigned ValueID = Record[0];
5685 uint64_t ModuleId = Record[1];
5686 uint64_t RawFlags = Record[2];
5687 unsigned RefArrayStart = 3;
5688 GlobalVarSummary::GVarFlags GVF;
5689 auto Flags = getDecodedGVSummaryFlags(RawFlags, Version);
5690 if (Version >= 5) {
5691 GVF = getDecodedGVarFlags(Record[3]);
5692 RefArrayStart = 4;
5693 }
5694 std::vector<ValueInfo> Refs =
5695 makeRefList(ArrayRef<uint64_t>(Record).slice(RefArrayStart));
5696 auto FS =
5697 llvm::make_unique<GlobalVarSummary>(Flags, GVF, std::move(Refs));
5698 LastSeenSummary = FS.get();
5699 FS->setModulePath(ModuleIdMap[ModuleId]);
5700 ValueInfo VI = getValueInfoFromValueId(ValueID).first;
5701 LastSeenGUID = VI.getGUID();
5702 TheIndex.addGlobalValueSummary(VI, std::move(FS));
5703 break;
5704 }
5705 // FS_COMBINED_ORIGINAL_NAME: [original_name]
5706 case bitc::FS_COMBINED_ORIGINAL_NAME: {
5707 uint64_t OriginalName = Record[0];
5708 if (!LastSeenSummary)
5709 return error("Name attachment that does not follow a combined record");
5710 LastSeenSummary->setOriginalName(OriginalName);
5711 TheIndex.addOriginalName(LastSeenGUID, OriginalName);
5712 // Reset the LastSeenSummary
5713 LastSeenSummary = nullptr;
5714 LastSeenGUID = 0;
5715 break;
5716 }
5717 case bitc::FS_TYPE_TESTS:
5718 assert(PendingTypeTests.empty());
5719 PendingTypeTests.insert(PendingTypeTests.end(), Record.begin(),
5720 Record.end());
5721 break;
5722
5723 case bitc::FS_TYPE_TEST_ASSUME_VCALLS:
5724 assert(PendingTypeTestAssumeVCalls.empty());
5725 for (unsigned I = 0; I != Record.size(); I += 2)
5726 PendingTypeTestAssumeVCalls.push_back({Record[I], Record[I+1]});
5727 break;
5728
5729 case bitc::FS_TYPE_CHECKED_LOAD_VCALLS:
5730 assert(PendingTypeCheckedLoadVCalls.empty());
5731 for (unsigned I = 0; I != Record.size(); I += 2)
5732 PendingTypeCheckedLoadVCalls.push_back({Record[I], Record[I+1]});
5733 break;
5734
5735 case bitc::FS_TYPE_TEST_ASSUME_CONST_VCALL:
5736 PendingTypeTestAssumeConstVCalls.push_back(
5737 {{Record[0], Record[1]}, {Record.begin() + 2, Record.end()}});
5738 break;
5739
5740 case bitc::FS_TYPE_CHECKED_LOAD_CONST_VCALL:
5741 PendingTypeCheckedLoadConstVCalls.push_back(
5742 {{Record[0], Record[1]}, {Record.begin() + 2, Record.end()}});
5743 break;
5744
5745 case bitc::FS_CFI_FUNCTION_DEFS: {
5746 std::set<std::string> &CfiFunctionDefs = TheIndex.cfiFunctionDefs();
5747 for (unsigned I = 0; I != Record.size(); I += 2)
5748 CfiFunctionDefs.insert(
5749 {Strtab.data() + Record[I], static_cast<size_t>(Record[I + 1])});
5750 break;
5751 }
5752
5753 case bitc::FS_CFI_FUNCTION_DECLS: {
5754 std::set<std::string> &CfiFunctionDecls = TheIndex.cfiFunctionDecls();
5755 for (unsigned I = 0; I != Record.size(); I += 2)
5756 CfiFunctionDecls.insert(
5757 {Strtab.data() + Record[I], static_cast<size_t>(Record[I + 1])});
5758 break;
5759 }
5760
5761 case bitc::FS_TYPE_ID:
5762 parseTypeIdSummaryRecord(Record, Strtab, TheIndex);
5763 break;
5764 }
5765 }
5766 llvm_unreachable("Exit infinite loop");
5767}

5769// Parse the module string table block into the Index.
5770// This populates the ModulePathStringTable map in the index.
5771Error ModuleSummaryIndexBitcodeReader::parseModuleStringTable() {
5772 if (Stream.EnterSubBlock(bitc::MODULE_STRTAB_BLOCK_ID))
5773 return error("Invalid record");
5774
5775 SmallVector<uint64_t, 64> Record;
5776
5777 SmallString<128> ModulePath;
5778 ModuleSummaryIndex::ModuleInfo *LastSeenModule = nullptr;
5779
5780 while (true) {
5781 BitstreamEntry Entry = Stream.advanceSkippingSubblocks();
5782
5783 switch (Entry.Kind) {
5784 case BitstreamEntry::SubBlock: // Handled for us already.
5785 case BitstreamEntry::Error:
5786 return error("Malformed block");
5787 case BitstreamEntry::EndBlock:
5788 return Error::success();
5789 case BitstreamEntry::Record:
5790 // The interesting case.
5791 break;
5792 }
5793
5794 Record.clear();
5795 switch (Stream.readRecord(Entry.ID, Record)) {
5796 default: // Default behavior: ignore.
5797 break;
5798 case bitc::MST_CODE_ENTRY: {
5799 // MST_ENTRY: [modid, namechar x N]
5800 uint64_t ModuleId = Record[0];
5801
5802 if (convertToString(Record, 1, ModulePath))
5803 return error("Invalid record");
5804
5805 LastSeenModule = TheIndex.addModule(ModulePath, ModuleId);
5806 ModuleIdMap[ModuleId] = LastSeenModule->first();
5807
5808 ModulePath.clear();
5809 break;
5810 }
5811 /// MST_CODE_HASH: [5*i32]
5812 case bitc::MST_CODE_HASH: {
5813 if (Record.size() != 5)
5814 return error("Invalid hash length " + Twine(Record.size()).str());
5815 if (!LastSeenModule)
5816 return error("Invalid hash that does not follow a module path");
5817 int Pos = 0;
5818 for (auto &Val : Record) {
5819 assert(!(Val >> 32) && "Unexpected high bits set");
5820 LastSeenModule->second.second[Pos++] = Val;
5821 }
5822 // Reset LastSeenModule to avoid overriding the hash unexpectedly.
5823 LastSeenModule = nullptr;
5824 break;
5825 }
5826 }
5827 }
5828 llvm_unreachable("Exit infinite loop");
5829}

5858
5859static Expected<StringRef> readBlobInRecord(BitstreamCursor &Stream,
5860 unsigned Block, unsigned RecordID) {
5861 if (Stream.EnterSubBlock(Block))
5862 return error("Invalid record");
5863
5864 StringRef Strtab;
5865 while (true) {
5866 BitstreamEntry Entry = Stream.advance();
5867 switch (Entry.Kind) {
5868 case BitstreamEntry::EndBlock:
5869 return Strtab;
5870
5871 case BitstreamEntry::Error:
5872 return error("Malformed block");
5873
5874 case BitstreamEntry::SubBlock:
5875 if (Stream.SkipBlock())
5876 return error("Malformed block");
5877 break;
5878
5879 case BitstreamEntry::Record:
5880 StringRef Blob;
5881 SmallVector<uint64_t, 1> Record;
5882 if (Stream.readRecord(Entry.ID, Record, &Blob) == RecordID)
5883 Strtab = Blob;
5884 break;
5885 }
5886 }
5887}

5900
5901Expected<BitcodeFileContents>
5902llvm::getBitcodeFileContents(MemoryBufferRef Buffer) {
5903 Expected<BitstreamCursor> StreamOrErr = initStream(Buffer);
5904 if (!StreamOrErr)
5905 return StreamOrErr.takeError();
5906 BitstreamCursor &Stream = *StreamOrErr;
5907
5908 BitcodeFileContents F;
5909 while (true) {
5910 uint64_t BCBegin = Stream.getCurrentByteNo();
5911
5912 // We may be consuming bitcode from a client that leaves garbage at the end
5913 // of the bitcode stream (e.g. Apple's ar tool). If we are close enough to
5914 // the end that there cannot possibly be another module, stop looking.
5915 if (BCBegin + 8 >= Stream.getBitcodeBytes().size())
5916 return F;
5917
5918 BitstreamEntry Entry = Stream.advance();
5919 switch (Entry.Kind) {
5920 case BitstreamEntry::EndBlock:
5921 case BitstreamEntry::Error:
5922 return error("Malformed block");
5923
5924 case BitstreamEntry::SubBlock: {
5925 uint64_t IdentificationBit = -1ull;
5926 if (Entry.ID == bitc::IDENTIFICATION_BLOCK_ID) {
5927 IdentificationBit = Stream.GetCurrentBitNo() - BCBegin * 8;
5928 if (Stream.SkipBlock())
5929 return error("Malformed block");
5930
5931 Entry = Stream.advance();
5932 if (Entry.Kind != BitstreamEntry::SubBlock ||
5933 Entry.ID != bitc::MODULE_BLOCK_ID)
5934 return error("Malformed block");
5935 }
5936
5937 if (Entry.ID == bitc::MODULE_BLOCK_ID) {
5938 uint64_t ModuleBit = Stream.GetCurrentBitNo() - BCBegin * 8;
5939 if (Stream.SkipBlock())
5940 return error("Malformed block");
5941
5942 F.Mods.push_back({Stream.getBitcodeBytes().slice(
5943 BCBegin, Stream.getCurrentByteNo() - BCBegin),
5944 Buffer.getBufferIdentifier(), IdentificationBit,
5945 ModuleBit});
5946 continue;
5947 }
5948
5949 if (Entry.ID == bitc::STRTAB_BLOCK_ID) {
5950 Expected<StringRef> Strtab =
5951 readBlobInRecord(Stream, bitc::STRTAB_BLOCK_ID, bitc::STRTAB_BLOB);
5952 if (!Strtab)
5953 return Strtab.takeError();
5954 // This string table is used by every preceding bitcode module that does
5955 // not have its own string table. A bitcode file may have multiple
5956 // string tables if it was created by binary concatenation, for example
5957 // with "llvm-cat -b".
5958 for (auto I = F.Mods.rbegin(), E = F.Mods.rend(); I != E; ++I) {
5959 if (!I->Strtab.empty())
5960 break;
5961 I->Strtab = *Strtab;
5962 }
5963 // Similarly, the string table is used by every preceding symbol table;
5964 // normally there will be just one unless the bitcode file was created
5965 // by binary concatenation.
5966 if (!F.Symtab.empty() && F.StrtabForSymtab.empty())
5967 F.StrtabForSymtab = *Strtab;
5968 continue;
5969 }
5970
5971 if (Entry.ID == bitc::SYMTAB_BLOCK_ID) {
5972 Expected<StringRef> SymtabOrErr =
5973 readBlobInRecord(Stream, bitc::SYMTAB_BLOCK_ID, bitc::SYMTAB_BLOB);
5974 if (!SymtabOrErr)
5975 return SymtabOrErr.takeError();
5976
5977 // We can expect the bitcode file to have multiple symbol tables if it
5978 // was created by binary concatenation. In that case we silently
5979 // ignore any subsequent symbol tables, which is fine because this is a
5980 // low level function. The client is expected to notice that the number
5981 // of modules in the symbol table does not match the number of modules
5982 // in the input file and regenerate the symbol table.
5983 if (F.Symtab.empty())
5984 F.Symtab = *SymtabOrErr;
5985 continue;
5986 }
5987
5988 if (Stream.SkipBlock())
5989 return error("Malformed block");
5990 continue;
5991 }
5992 case BitstreamEntry::Record:
5993 Stream.skipRecord(Entry.ID);
5994 continue;
5995 }
5996 }
5997}

5999/// Get a lazy one-at-time loading module from bitcode.
6000///
6001/// This isn't always used in a lazy context. In particular, it's also used by
6002/// \a parseModule(). If this is truly lazy, then we need to eagerly pull
6003/// in forward-referenced functions from block address references.
6004///
6005/// \param[in] MaterializeAll Set to \c true if we should materialize
6006/// everything.
6007Expected<std::unique_ptr<Module>>
6008BitcodeModule::getModuleImpl(LLVMContext &Context, bool MaterializeAll,
6009 bool ShouldLazyLoadMetadata, bool IsImporting) {
6010 BitstreamCursor Stream(Buffer);
6011
6012 std::string ProducerIdentification;
6013 if (IdentificationBit != -1ull) {
6014 Stream.JumpToBit(IdentificationBit);
6015 Expected<std::string> ProducerIdentificationOrErr =
6016 readIdentificationBlock(Stream);
6017 if (!ProducerIdentificationOrErr)
6018 return ProducerIdentificationOrErr.takeError();
6019
6020 ProducerIdentification = *ProducerIdentificationOrErr;
6021 }
6022
6023 Stream.JumpToBit(ModuleBit);
6024 auto *R = new BitcodeReader(std::move(Stream), Strtab, ProducerIdentification,
6025 Context);
6026
6027 std::unique_ptr<Module> M =
6028 llvm::make_unique<Module>(ModuleIdentifier, Context);
6029 M->setMaterializer(R);
6030
6031 // Delay parsing Metadata if ShouldLazyLoadMetadata is true.
6032 if (Error Err =
6033 R->parseBitcodeInto(M.get(), ShouldLazyLoadMetadata, IsImporting))
6034 return std::move(Err);
6035
6036 if (MaterializeAll) {
6037 // Read in the entire module, and destroy the BitcodeReader.
6038 if (Error Err = M->materializeAll())
6039 return std::move(Err);
6040 } else {
6041 // Resolve forward references from blockaddresses.
6042 if (Error Err = R->materializeForwardReferencedFunctions())
6043 return std::move(Err);
6044 }
6045 return std::move(M);
6046}
6047
6048Expected<std::unique_ptr<Module>>
6049BitcodeModule::getLazyModule(LLVMContext &Context, bool ShouldLazyLoadMetadata,
6050 bool IsImporting) {
6051 return getModuleImpl(Context, false, ShouldLazyLoadMetadata, IsImporting);
6052}

6054// Parse the specified bitcode buffer and merge the index into CombinedIndex.
6055// We don't use ModuleIdentifier here because the client may need to control the
6056// module path used in the combined summary (e.g. when reading summaries for
6057// regular LTO modules).
6058Error BitcodeModule::readSummary(ModuleSummaryIndex &CombinedIndex,
6059 StringRef ModulePath, uint64_t ModuleId) {
6060 BitstreamCursor Stream(Buffer);
6061 Stream.JumpToBit(ModuleBit);
6062
6063 ModuleSummaryIndexBitcodeReader R(std::move(Stream), Strtab, CombinedIndex,
6064 ModulePath, ModuleId);

6068// Parse the specified bitcode buffer, returning the function info index.
6069Expected<std::unique_ptr<ModuleSummaryIndex>> BitcodeModule::getSummary() {
6070 BitstreamCursor Stream(Buffer);
6071 Stream.JumpToBit(ModuleBit);
6072

6083static Expected<bool> getEnableSplitLTOUnitFlag(BitstreamCursor &Stream,
6084 unsigned ID) {
6085 if (Stream.EnterSubBlock(ID))
6086 return error("Invalid record");
6087 SmallVector<uint64_t, 64> Record;
6088
6089 while (true) {
6090 BitstreamEntry Entry = Stream.advanceSkippingSubblocks();
6091
6092 switch (Entry.Kind) {
6093 case BitstreamEntry::SubBlock: // Handled for us already.
6094 case BitstreamEntry::Error:
6095 return error("Malformed block");
6096 case BitstreamEntry::EndBlock:
6097 // If no flags record found, conservatively return true to mimic
6098 // behavior before this flag was added.
6099 return true;
6100 case BitstreamEntry::Record:
6101 // The interesting case.
6102 break;
6103 }
6104
6105 // Look for the FS_FLAGS record.
6106 Record.clear();
6107 auto BitCode = Stream.readRecord(Entry.ID, Record);
6108 switch (BitCode) {
6109 default: // Default behavior: ignore.
6110 break;
6111 case bitc::FS_FLAGS: { // [flags]
6112 uint64_t Flags = Record[0];
6113 // Scan flags.
6114 assert(Flags <= 0x1f && "Unexpected bits in flag");
6115
6116 return Flags & 0x8;
6117 }
6118 }
6119 }
6120 llvm_unreachable("Exit infinite loop");
6121}

6123// Check if the given bitcode buffer contains a global value summary block.
6124Expected<BitcodeLTOInfo> BitcodeModule::getLTOInfo() {
6125 BitstreamCursor Stream(Buffer);
6126 Stream.JumpToBit(ModuleBit);
6127
6128 if (Stream.EnterSubBlock(bitc::MODULE_BLOCK_ID))
6129 return error("Invalid record");
6130
6131 while (true) {
6132 BitstreamEntry Entry = Stream.advance();
6133
6134 switch (Entry.Kind) {
6135 case BitstreamEntry::Error:
6136 return error("Malformed block");
6137 case BitstreamEntry::EndBlock:
6138 return BitcodeLTOInfo{/*IsThinLTO=*/false, /*HasSummary=*/false,
6139 /*EnableSplitLTOUnit=*/false};
6140
6141 case BitstreamEntry::SubBlock:
6142 if (Entry.ID == bitc::GLOBALVAL_SUMMARY_BLOCK_ID) {
6143 Expected<bool> EnableSplitLTOUnit =
6144 getEnableSplitLTOUnitFlag(Stream, Entry.ID);
6145 if (!EnableSplitLTOUnit)
6146 return EnableSplitLTOUnit.takeError();
6147 return BitcodeLTOInfo{/*IsThinLTO=*/true, /*HasSummary=*/true,
6148 *EnableSplitLTOUnit};
6149 }
6150
6151 if (Entry.ID == bitc::FULL_LTO_GLOBALVAL_SUMMARY_BLOCK_ID) {
6152 Expected<bool> EnableSplitLTOUnit =
6153 getEnableSplitLTOUnitFlag(Stream, Entry.ID);
6154 if (!EnableSplitLTOUnit)
6155 return EnableSplitLTOUnit.takeError();
6156 return BitcodeLTOInfo{/*IsThinLTO=*/false, /*HasSummary=*/true,
6157 *EnableSplitLTOUnit};
6158 }
6159
6160 // Ignore other sub-blocks.
6161 if (Stream.SkipBlock())
6162 return error("Malformed block");
6163 continue;
6164
6165 case BitstreamEntry::Record:
6166 Stream.skipRecord(Entry.ID);
6167 continue;
6168 }
6169 }
6170}
